title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 9-inch square pan with cooking spray.
In large bowl combine dry ingredients until well mixed. In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth. Pour into pans.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.	Stir in flour, salt, pepper and fresh mushrooms.	Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup and simmer 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve in ring of poppy seed noodles on hot platter.
Garnish with parsley bouquet.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chew bread
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar. Mix together. Then add butter and mix. To this, add flour, vanilla and nuts and mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Add 1 egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat after each.
Continue to alternate ingredients until all have been added.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hunter's delight
directions: The day before you are ready to serve, cut venison into 2 or 3-inch strips.
Place in marinating container and cover with soy sauce.
Next day, take strips of meat, wrap with bacon and secure with round toothpick.
Cook on charcoal grill until done.
Don't overcook.
This is very good for a party food.

title: smokehouse barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate in covered glass jar.
Keeps a long time.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: sausage cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased baking dish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve hot.
Can be cooked ahead, cool and freeze.
Put in oven long enough to warm just before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to instructions on box.
Add marshmallows, walnuts and strawberries.
Chill until firm.

title: green pepper swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into serving size pieces.
Dip in flour and brown in large skillet in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add remaining ingredients except cornstarch and water.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Thicken gravy with cornstarch and water mixture. This is also good served on rice.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: In saucepan brown beef and onions.
Stir to separate meat. Pour off fat.
Stir in 3/4 cup cheese and remaining ingredients. Spoon into casserole; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Makes 4 servings.)

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Use 4 cups of raw rhubarb cut in 1-inch cubes (place in 9 x 13-inch dish).
Sprinkle 3 ounce box of strawberry Jell-O (dry) over rhubarb.
Spread evenly 1 cup of sugar over rhubarb.
Use 1 box of dry white cake mix poured evenly over rhubarb.
DO NOT STIR INGREDIENTS TOGETHER.
Pour over 1 cup melted margarine and 1 cup of water.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to an hour until golden brown.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: cuban hash
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Add meat and cook until brown; drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: death by chocolate ii
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sour cream, oil, water and eggs; stir well.
Add cake and pudding; mix well.
Add chips and mix well.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Mix Oreo crumbs and butter.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 cup for top.
Combine cream cheese and Cool Whip. Spread over crumbs.
Mix milk and pudding.
Spread over mixture. Spread with remaining Cool Whip.
Top with remaining crumbs.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Combine apples, cranberries and 2 tablespoons flour, tossing to coat. Add 1 cup white sugar and mix well.
Place in 2-quart casserole. Combine oatmeal, pecans, 1/2 cup flour and brown sugar. Add butter and stir well. Spoon over fruit mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for Christmas brunch.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 2 teaspoons spiced tea mix to 1 cup of boiling water.
Use cinnamon stick to stir.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Mix as for regular cookies.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown. Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: deluxe cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar, butter and cinnamon in a bowl; mix well.
Press into a 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for layers.
Bake 45 minutes or less for long pan.
Ice with caramel icing.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes.
Mix all ingredients except raisins and coconut in large mixing bowl.
Put sweet potatoes in greased pan (grease with 1/2 stick butter).
Add raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour rest of ingredients over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until golden brown.
After cooked about 30 minutes, take out and stir mixture well and put back in oven and finish cooking.

title: corned beef hash quiche
directions: In a bowl, mix hash, bread crumbs and one egg.
Mix well. Spread in a 9-inch pie plate.
Press mixture up to the rim.
Toss cheese and flour and sprinkle on top of hash.
Combine remaining 3 eggs, milk and pepper.
Pour into hash lined plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until egg mixture is set.

title: layered salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite size pieces and place in an 8 x 10-inch square dish.
Pour drained peas on top.
Place celery over peas.
Place onions over celery.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise over celery.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: christmas pudding candy
directions: Put through food chopper into a large bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Cook to soft ball stage and add vanilla.
Beat until creamy and cool.
Pour sauce over fruit mixture and mix thoroughly.
Form into logs 1-inch in diameter and desired length.
Roll each log in a damp cloth and then in aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator at least one month. Will keep for a full year.
Makes 10 to 12 pounds of candy.

title: ed's macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix milk, paprika, butter and eggs in bowl or blender. Spray oil in casserole cooking dish. Cook macaroni noodles and drain. Mix Velveeta cheese with noodles while hot and place in dish. Pour milk and egg mixture over noodles. If desired, add sliced or grated Cheddar cheese over macaroni. Place in a 350° oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: onion pie
directions: This is a great way to use shriner's Vidalia onions.

title: creamy apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix and butter; mix until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup for topping.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon to reserved topping mix.
Mix well; set aside.

title: hamburger macaroni bake
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Lightly cook hamburger and onion until tender.
Stir in soup, water, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from stove and stir in macaroni and cheese. Pour in casserole.
Cover top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Wash rice; combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat tomato soup and water.
Bake in the oven 45 minutes to an hour at 350° or until done.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs and cream with the sugar.
Add Wesson oil and mix well. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to the other mixture and cream well. Add the prunes and chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° for 1 hour.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: hawaiian haystack
directions: Combine soup and Chicken Broth in a medium saucepan to make gravy.
Stir to blend.
Add Chicken Mix.
Simmer about 8 to 10 minutes, until heated through.
On 8 individual serving plates layer all ingredients.
First stack rice, chow mein noodles and chicken and gravy.
Add tomatoes, celery, green pepper and green onion.
Top this with pineapple chunks, grated Cheddar cheese and more chicken and gravy, if desired. Stack almonds, coconut and pimiento on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chinese hot and sour soup
directions: Cover first 3 ingredients with water; soak for 20 minutes. Drain and squeeze dry.
Cut mushrooms and tofu into slivers and add to beef stock, along with cloud ears and lilybuds.
Bring to a boil; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with the cold beef stock and stir into the soup until the mixture becomes thickened and clear.
Add soy sauce, pepper and vinegar.
Set aside until ready to serve.
Heat to simmering.
Mix egg with water and pour into soup.
Float oils on top of soup.
Serve immediately.

title: seafood pronencake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Place in oven to melt.
Do not brown butter.
Place shrimp and vegetables in dish.
Stir to coat with butter.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until shrimp are opaque. Do not overcook.
Serve on rice.

title: no hassle stew
directions: 1. Place all ingredients in a pot of boiling water. Cover pot and walk away.
2. Stew will be finished when you come back the next day.

title: no bake peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan and cook until it comes to a boil.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and coconut. Before it cools, drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let cool; store in airtight container.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with dry Ranch dressing mix.
Spread thick layer of cream cheese mixture on party rye.
Place cucumber slice on cream cheese.
Sprinkle with dill weed for flavor and appearance.

title: chocolate banana pudding
directions: Use leftover biscuits or a loaf of old bread; crumble. Add sugar to taste and cinnamon to taste. Add enough boiling water to be like a cake batter. Pour in baking dish and bake until firm, about 1 hour at 350°.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs, sugar, salt, butter, syrup and cream.
Stir in vanilla, brandy and pecans.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is golden brown.
Cool. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Slice
bread
and
soak
in milk and cream.
Crush with hands until
well mixed.	Add beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and raisins. Stir
well.
Melt the butter in bottom of pan (9 1/2 x 13-inch). Pour
batter
into	pan.
Bake
for 45 minutes or until fork comes out clean at 325° to 350°.	(Start with 350°; turn heat down after 45 minutes if not done.)

title: french toast custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly; blend in milk, sugar and vanilla.
Brown French toast (using some of the oleo).
Quarter the toast slices and keep in the oven.
In an 8 or 10-inch Corningware dish, pour the remaining egg mixture and cook 2 minutes on medium heat.
Put in the toast quarters by standing on end.
Cover pan and cook until set.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or cinnamon.
Serve with warm strawberries.

title: old-fashioned pot roast
directions: Sprinkle the roast with 1 tablespoon flour.
In a Dutch oven, brown the roast on all sides in half of the margarine.
Add the water, bouillon, onion, celery, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add carrots; cover and simmer for 1 hour longer or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and carrots to a serving platter and keep warm.
You may strain cooking juices (if desired) and set aside.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Melt Velveeta cheese in separate containers.
When cheese is melted, mix Ro-Tel and tomato paste.
Stir until mixed completely.
Add hamburger and onion; let dip simmer, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Pour over nacho chips.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add molasses and egg, beating until light and fluffy. Stir in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Arrange on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will crack on top and settle slightly when done.
Remove to wire rack to cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Blend flour; cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth and milk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in vegetables, seasonings and egg.
Heat.
Spoon chicken mixture into a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with pastry; cut slits in pastry to let steam escape.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until pastry is golden brown.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
(If you like onion, add a few slices of onion in the blender for flavor.)
Fry and enjoy with sugar, syrup or fresh strawberry jam.

title: greasy fried potatoes
directions: Wash and slice potatoes; do not peel.
Heat Crisco in cast iron skillet.
Saute onions; add potatoes.
Over medium heat, fry until golden brown.
Do not overcook.
Season to taste.

title: party mix
directions: Mix melted butter, Orville Redenbacher's oil and seasonings together and pour over already mixed dry ingredients (in large trash bag). if you have a favorite cracker, you may exchange for one on the list.
Mix at least 24 hours before serving, allowing seasonings to flavor ingredients.
You do not have to bake this. Enjoy!

title: ramen vegetable steak stir-fry
directions: In medium bowl, combine beef strips, garlic, 1 tablespoon sesame oil and ground pepper; toss to coat.
Set aside.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Wash, quarter and cut out hard core of cabbage; slice thin. Slice onion and bell pepper into thin slices.
Dissolve chicken bouillons in boiling water.
Add cabbage, pepper and onion; cook for 10 minutes.
Serves about 5.

title: veggie soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large 6 to 8-quart pot.
Fill with water and cook until veggies are tender or desired doneness. Season to your taste.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Add refried beans and taco sauce.
Mix well.
In a 12 x 2 x 9-inch pan, fill each tortilla shell; roll and place in pan.
Fill pan with leftover mix on top.
Cover with enchilada sauce and aluminum foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Uncover and add cheese. Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: cheese cake salad
directions: Place above ingredients in large 9 X 13 cake pan and chill until firm.

title: huevos rancheros(microwave recipe)
directions: Turn selector control to "Normal".
Place bacon drippings and onions in 2-quart ovenware casserole.
Cook 7 to 8 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add chiles and tomatoes.
Continue cooking at "Normal" until some of the juices have cooked down, about 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add cheese cubes and stir. Whey they are almost melted, drop in eggs, one at a time.
Cover.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put egg whites, sugar, water and cream of tartar in the top part of a double boiler over boiling water.
Beat with electric beater at high speed until mixture is thick and creamy, about 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and continue beating until very smooth and glossy.
Add vanilla and beat again to blend.
Spread on cake. Enough for tops and sides of an 8-inch or 9-inch 2-layer cake. Must be prepared just before cake is ready to be frosted.

title: grated cheese and potatoes
directions: Slice thin potatoes in casserole dish.
Spread cheese over potatoes.
Melt sour cream, butter, salt and pepper over low heat and pour over cheese.
Bake until hot and bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix eggs, bananas and shortening.
Add vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and soda which has been mixed together very well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Makes 1 loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Set aside.
Mix together sugars, butter, eggs and peanut butter.
Stir flour mixture into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a spoon onto baking pan. Flatten with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in balls about the size of a large marble (roll in palm of hand to make them tighter so they won't spread as much when baking).
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until brown.
Makes approximately 175 balls.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Saute onion; add chilies and simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add milk, water and soda.
Stir and add cheese.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Cook potatoes until done.
Layer potatoes, onion and hamburger.
Top with 1/2 can of both soups.
Repeat ingredients again.

title: party potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add softened cream cheese to sour cream and mix with a mixer.
Add instant potatoes; blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brush top with melted butter and sprinkle top with paprika and garlic salt.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 12 servings.

title: kid-licious lasagne
directions: Alternate layers, beginning with sauce on bottom of 9 x 13 pan (baking dish). Follow with 3 or 4 noodles, depending on size of pan. Mix browned hamburger into remaining spaghetti sauce. Layer sauce, cottage cheese, then 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese. Follow with another noodle layer, sauce, more cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese, then finish with a layer of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes and let cool before serving.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Add flavorings.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jambalaya
directions: Depending on size of pot, cover bottom with cooking oil.
Add onions and brown.
Add tomato sauce and garlic.
Cook until this changes to a red, red color.
Add same amounts of shrimp, ham and smoked sausage.
Cook for 10 minutes on medium heat.
Add rice and water.
Cook until rice is done.
Careful cooking this, it sticks to bottom of pan very easily.

title: chocolate kisses(makes 16)
directions: You also need oven, 2 medium bowls, mixer, 2 spoons, baking sheet and parchment sheets.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Thoroughly grease a 9-inch cake pan or cast-iron skillet.
In a large bowl put flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix.
Work in shortening as for pie dough.
Quickly stir in milk; add raisins and caraway seed.
Stir to distribute evenly.
Knead about 20 times on a floured surface (shape).
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: fried potatoes
directions: Sprinkle cornflake crumbs and grated Parmesan cheese over sliced potatoes while you are frying them.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain and layer vegetables in order given in a baking dish. Combine soup, sour cream, onion and cheese.
Spread over layered vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with Ritz crackers, mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: family affair
directions: Mix and bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box.
Mix jello as directed and let set slightly.
Stir in strawberries and gel completely.
Mix pudding per directions on box with milk.
Use a medium size punch bowl.
Layer jello, layer cake (cut in pieces), layer pudding, then Cool Whip.
Keep layering until bowl is full. Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: cracker jack popcorn or peanut brittle
directions: Cover saucepan with water.
Add Karo syrup, sugar and salt. Boil until slightly beige.
Add butter.
Keep stirring and cooking over medium heat until it browns to orange color.
(It will have a burned smell.)
Add soda.
Stir quickly and pour over dishpan of popcorn, or, pour over sheet pan with bottom covered with hulless peanuts for peanut brittle.

title: sweetened condensed
directions: Combine in the blender.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter casserole dish.
Drain tomatoes. Add flour to tomato liquid to make a paste.
Combine tomatoes, paste, croutons, celery seed and parsley.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes.
In the meantime, combine bread crumbs, cheese and butter.
Remove from oven; cover top with crumb mixture.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 4.

title: hot cheddar cheese dip
directions: Grate cheese; grate onion.
In a glass serving dish, add all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with assorted crackers or breads.

title: di's french green bean surprise
directions: Chop red and green peppers and onion.
Melt butter in pan and saute all ingredients until tender.
Makes 14 to 16 side servings.

title: holiday green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 of onions.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in bean mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin loaf
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl, and add remainder of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 1 lb. greased coffee cans.
Will fill approximately 6 cans.
Fill each can 1/2 full, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious served with whipped cream, or a hot sauce.
Freezes well.

title: green beans with sage
directions: Trim green beans. Cook beans in boiling water, salted, until tender, about 10 minutes.
In the hot pot, melt butter with 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and the sage. Add the green beans and toss to coat.

title: biscuits
directions: Using a pastry cutter (or fork, if you don't have a pastry cutter), cut the Crisco into the flour until it resembles coarse crumbs. Blend in enough milk to make a soft dough. Turn out on a lightly floured surface. Knead gently for 30 seconds. Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut with a biscuit cutter. Bake at 475° on an ungreased baking sheet for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Makes about 12 biscuits.

title: stan musial's maple barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Boil.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add barbecue sauce, catsup, brown sugar, syrup and seasonings.
Stir well and boil.
If too thick, add about 1 cup water.
(Makes 8 cups.)

title: creme de menthe cooler
directions: Boil sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour into large bowl. Cool.
Add orange juice, lemonade, pineapple and creme de menthe. Chill.
In each glass, fill with ice cubes and pour in 1/2 cup mixture and fill with ginger ale.
Serves 20.

title: mexican appetizer
directions: Blend together cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise. Spread over a 9-inch plate.
Spread taco sauce over cheese mixture on plate.
Place remaining ingredients on mixture with the cheese and tomatoes being last.
Let it sit overnight to allow the taco sauce to blend into the cheese mixture.
Serve with taco chips.

title: christmas pecans
directions: Mix butter, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Add pecans to mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Keep turning.
Cool on wax paper.

title: corn on the cob with herb butter
directions: Line bottom of large kettle with clean corn husks.
Top with corn.
Add 1-inch boiling water.
Cover tightly and steam 6 to 8 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: hungarian easter cheese
directions: Pour milk into saucepan and bring to a boil.
Beat eggs slightly and add gradually to milk.
Cook over low heat about 8 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture into cheesecloth and tie tightly, forming a ball.
Hang and let drain into pan for 2 to 4 hours.
Remove from cheesecloth; cover with dampened cloth and refrigerate.

title: butter baked rice
directions: Combine salt and 2 cups water.
Boil and pour over rice.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Rinse rice with cold water; drain well.

title: chicken spaghetti delight
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling chicken broth 4 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Saute pepper and onion in hot oil until soft.
Melt butter in saucepan; add slowly flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly, and cook over medium heat until it boils.
Remove from heat; add cheese and undrained mushrooms.
Combine spaghetti, sauteed vegetables, cheese sauce and chicken.
Put in greased casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese last 10 minutes if desired.

title: quesadillas
directions: Drain chicken.
Mash into finely ground pieces and mix with seasoning mix.
Place thin layer of chicken on a tortilla; top with grated cheese.
Place another tortilla on top of the first. Place quesadilla in dry skillet (or may add small amount of butter). Brown on both sides.
Remove from heat; cut into fourths. Serve with sour cream, salsa or guacamole.

title: easy and delicious upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in a large skillet.
Place pineapple slices in the bottom of the skillet.
Place the cherry halves in the center of the pineapple.
Mix the other ingredients together and pour into the skillet.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 35 minutes.
Turn cake out of skillet.

title: capon and bread dressing
directions: Rinse the capon and pat dry.
Rub with the seasoned salt, seasoned pepper and paprika.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; save juice.
Break up chicken.
Mix all ingredients except soups and milk.
Heat soups and milk.
Put chicken on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then pour warm soups and milk on chicken.
Mix rest of ingredients with chicken broth, then pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sour cream - blueberry pancakes
directions: Combine milk, egg and sour cream. Beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Add to milk mixture. Beat just until large lumps disappear. Stir in the butter. Fold in the blueberries. For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter into a hot, lightly greased griddle or skillet. Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are slightly dry. Serve with blueberry syrup, if desired. Yield: 12 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: the ultimate butter tart
directions: Hint:
Pastry recipe on back of Crisco shortening.

title: emma's pineapple cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet. Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Mix together brown sugar and white sugar. Combine the shortening, eggs and vanilla with the dry ingredients. Mix all above ingredients together, then add nuts, raisins, pineapple and chocolate chips. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Slowly cook mustard and jelly until mixed together.
Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until done.

title: just squash
directions: Rub a Teflon skillet with oil.
Line bottom of skillet with squash.
Top with onions and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat until squash is browned on the bottom, then flip over.
Cover and simmer until tender.

title: pecan cheese crispies
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Add hot sauce and mustard.
Add flour.
Stir in cereal; shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork, making a crisscross design.
Press pecan half in center.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and cook over low heat until thick.
Turn into a baked pie shell.
Whip egg whites with 3 tablespoon sugar.
Put on top of filling and bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: freezer date cookies(sugarless)
directions: Beat butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture; beat until blended.
Mix in dates, coconut and walnuts. Form into 2 (1 1/2-inch) rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill in freezer until firm, about 2 hours or up to a month.
Cut into 3/8-inch slices.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze all water out of it.
Mix spinach with mayonnaise, onions, bacon bits and Ranch dressing package.
Let set in fridge minimum of 2 hours before making.
Heat tortillas for 2 seconds in microwave (or steamer).
Spread mixture over tortilla and roll.
When all are fixed, slice into bite-size pieces. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: blue plum cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in Bundt pan or angel food cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Fry bacon; reserve fat.
Brown onion and water chestnuts in hot bacon fat.
Drain green beans (save 1/2 cup liquid); mix with remaining ingredients and add to onion in skillet.
Cook, stirring until boiling.
Add green beans to rest of ingredients and heat.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: salami
directions: *Two and one-half pounds of venison and 2 1/2 pounds of beef may be substituted for the 5 pounds of beef.

title: spenny's favorite chicken
directions: Cook onion in butter.
Stir in tomato soup, beer, curry powder, oregano
and pepper; bring to a boil, then let simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream together	sugar,	sour cream and butter.	Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat well.	Sift flour and soda together.
Beat egg
whites,
not
stiff.
Fold
in last vanilla and lemon.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Let set in pan 20 minutes.	Turn out
and
ice or eat plain.
Mellows as it sets if wrapped tightly.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients in bowl and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put oven on 325°.
Cook pie for one hour or until golden brown.

title: east indies salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package, omitting butter.
Add frozen peas and stir until peas are thawed.
About 1 hour before serving, combine mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder and onion. Mix well.
Measure 1/2 cup and set aside.
Add shrimp and celery to remaining dressing.
Then add the rice and mix lightly with a fork.
Chill.
Serve with reserved dressing on salad greens with tomato wedges.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind everything in food chopper except turmeric and pickling spice. Put into pot; boil 30 minutes. Add turmeric just before taking up. Should make 6 pints.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crescent rolls and croutons. Flatten the crescent rolls.
Put scoop of mixture inside each crescent roll and pinch together.
Sprinkle crushed croutons on top of pockets.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes in 350° oven. You can make ahead and freeze.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder. Cream sugar, margarine and butter until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Alternate flour mixture with milk. Add vanilla. Pour in greased and floured steeple pan and bake 1 hour at 325° or 350°. Usually takes a little longer!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into small bite-size balls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen and used at a later date.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add onion, green pepper, salt, chili mix and tomatoes.
Stir and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in corn and olives.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beer bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the sifted self-rising flour and sugar. Add beer.
It should be at room temperature.
Mix with spoon. Pour into loaf pan (small) that has been greased with butter. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
To make self-rising flour from regular flour:

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat.
Add sauce and water, salt and seasoning.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix in small bowl cottage cheese and eggs until blended.
Put 1/3 cup of meat in bottom, then noodles, then 1 cup cottage cheese, then Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat.
End with meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, then put more cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven cooking bag, large size.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mix banana, mayonnaise and sugar until well blended. Add flour and baking soda, mixing well. Pour into 8 muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Cut boiled eggs in halves and remove yolks. Mash yolks and blend with mayonnaise, sour cream and mustard. Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble. Chop egg whites and combine with bacon, onion, potatoes and Italian salad dressing. Fold in mayonnaise mixture. Season with salt and celery seed. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sensational italian dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in a quart jar.
Dressing will keep indefinitely in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour bean relish
directions: Drain and rinse all beans.
Mix together beans, onions, peppers and pimento.
Mix separately vinegar, oil, sugar and salt. Add vegetables and marinate for 24 hours.
Mix well before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Spread almonds in a single layer in shallow pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes, stirring often until almonds just begin to turn color.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie shell; set aside.
Bring 1 1/4 cups of water to a boil.
Add jello, sugar, cornstarch and Karo syrup.
Stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add in hulled, sliced strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: stuffed tomato appetizers
directions: Place tomatoes stem-side down on cutting board.
Make an x-cut to within 1/4-inch of bottom of each tomato; carefully spread to open.
In small bowl, combine cream cheese, dressing mix and milk; blend well.
Fill each tomato with heaping 1/2 teaspoon cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle tops with chopped parsley.
Refrigerate up to 6 hours before serving.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Chop peppers, leaving in seeds.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.
Mash through strainer to obtain more juice, then strain juice through cheesecloth in order to have clear jelly. Add sugar and vinegar to juice.
Bring rapidly to a boil and add lemon juice and Certo.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and skim off foam.

title: pie crust - 1963
directions: Blend together until crumbly mixture.
Add 3 tablespoons cold water.
Mix well (I use my hands).
Makes two crusts.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut apples into fourths.
Heat apples and water to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring to break up apples, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat until boiling and boil 1 minute.

title: white barbecue chicken
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, cayenne pepper and egg in blender. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place in single layer in glass dish. Pour marinade over chicken, turning to coat.
Cover and marinate 8 to 16 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain chicken, reserving marinade and place on rack.
Grill for 1 hour, turning and basting with reserved marinade.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Take half of cheese, bisquick, and sausage mix well. Roll on floured surface thin. Take rest of cheese and stuff peppers. Wrap dough around peppers. Roll in shake and bake. Bake @350 for almost 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together, put in 2 qt casserole.
Sprinkle with 1 pkg of crumbled Town House Crackers, top with 1 stick of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chips
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole #4
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add soup, onions, cheese, beaten eggs and
mayonnaise.
Place
casserole in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. (Crackers may be crumbled over the top before baking if preferred.)

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Mix the flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder and soda and salt in a large bowl.

title: all-purpose marinade
directions: Mix together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Use as marinade on meats and vegetables.
Must use low salt (sodium) soy sauce or it will be too salty.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: In a bowl, combine flour and sugar. Drain the pineapple, reserving 1 1/2 cups of juice. Add juice to flour mixture. Mix well. Stir in the pineapple and cheese. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and stir. Bake 10 minutes longer. Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over the pineapple mixture. Return to the oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut core from head of cabbage; peel off 12 leaves.
Cover with water; bring to boil, remove and drain.
Mix hamburger, egg, rice, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Fill each leaf and roll.
Put in baking pan and top with tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red potato salad
directions: Place potatoes, eggs, celery, black olives and pickles in large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir into potatoes and chill.
Leave skin on potatoes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place unopened can of milk in pot and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer for about 2 hours.
(Make sure water always covers pan.)
Cool.
Line bottom of crust with bananas.
Pour Eagle Brand over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
(May sprinkle Heath bar crumbs over top.)

title: mother williams wonderful chicken
directions: Chop chicken into chunks.
Lightly saute chicken, adding green and red pepper.
Also add sliced up onion, salt, pepper and cream of chicken soup.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes on low heat.

title: tom coon fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers and place in 6-quart mixing bowl, add nuts, raisins, candied fruits and cherries.
Cut marshmallows in half and place in top of double boiler.
Add orange juice and maraschino cherry juice.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add Peach Schnapps; remove marshmallow mixture from heat and beat with highest speed of electric mixer for 15 minutes.
Add graham cracker mixture and blend thoroughly.
Line 2 bread loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2-inch) with two strips of wax paper 3-inches above rim.
Turn fruitcake in to the pan.
Press with spoon, fold wax paper over cake and press down with hands.
Chill in refrigerator at least 8 hours before slicing.
Makes about 7 pounds fruit cake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough as directed on a pizza pan.
Let cool.
Mix the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over cookie.
Place fruit around the cookie.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together and top with bacon. Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool.
Remove bones.
Combine soup and broth.
Fix stuffing according to instructions on package. Put layer of chicken, soup and stuffing, ending up with stuffing on top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Add all at once.
Simmer all ingredients 10 minutes.
Remove onion before serving.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine ingredients, except cheese and potato chips.
Toss lightly.
Pile lightly into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and potato chips and bake in hot 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine first 11 ingredients.
Cover casserole tightly and bake in preheated 250° oven for 4 hours, then increase temperature to 300° and add water chestnuts, mushrooms and potatoes.
Bake 1 hour longer.

title: potato cakes
directions: To the mashed potatoes, add onion and bread that has been pulled into small pieces.
Mix well.
Shape into 6 thick cakes. Dip into beaten egg and fry in hot vegetable shortening (about 3 tablespoons).

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in a casserole dish.
Pour in mushroom soup and sprinkle with ground pepper.
Add milk.
Add French fried onions; mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook the cake mix by directions.
Put in layers in 1-inch pieces in a deep glass bowl.
Add other ingredients in layers. May may top with some Cool Whip and any of the following: coconut, bananas and pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine beaten eggs, soup, mayonnaise and onion in bowl and mix.
Stir in broccoli and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed celery sticks
directions: Cut celery into 3-inch pieces (make sure it's completely dry). Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread about 1 tablespoon in each piece of celery. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Makes about 14.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine zucchini, onion, tomato, Bisquick, grated cheese, salt, oregano and pepper.
Mix oil and eggs; add to first mixture. Grease casserole dish; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tammy's chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken pieces off.
Rinse broccoli.
Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Take a large casserole dish; put broccoli on bottom of entire dish.
Place rinsed chicken pieces on top of broccoli.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Add 2 cans of water.
Grate Cheddar cheese and sprinkle over entire dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious.

title: mock oysters rockefeller
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add all other ingredients except almonds.
Allow cheese to melt.
Top with almonds and serve hot from chafing dish with Triscuits.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and baking powder; set aside. Alternate adding flour mixture with the sour cream to the first mixture.
Sprinkle dropped cookies with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on a lightly greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven.
Do not overcook.

title: one egg cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll about 1 teaspoon of dough into small balls with floured hands.
Bake at 400° for 9 minutes. Frost when cool.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Sprinkle the gelatin over 1/4 cup milk; stir and let stand 5 minutes to soften.
In a heavy saucepan, whisk together 1 cup milk and the cocoa until well blended.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring.

In a small bowl, beat the remaining 1/4 cup milk, the cornstarch and egg yolk until smooth. Add this mixture to the cocoa mixture and continue cooking over low heat, stirring, until the mixture thickens, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove the saucepan from the heat, add the softened gelatin and the sweetener, and stir until dissolved.
Stir in the vanilla extract.
Chill until partially set.
In a mixing bowl, beat together the egg white, skim milk powder and 1/4 cup ice water until stiff peaks form.
Fold into the chocolate mixture. Spoon into the prepared pie shell.
Chill about 4 hours until set.

title: lemon snows
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly by hand.
Drop by teaspoon into a pan of powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.

title: hamburger bean boat
directions: Mix green beans and soup together.
Mix half of green bean mixture into hamburg.
Mix in bread crumbs.
Make large meatballs. Put each meatball into a large square of foil; make hole in center of each meatball.
Spoon in large spoonful of mixture. Fold foil up around hamburg.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 390°.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute onions. Cook chicken until no longer pink. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer or place in crock-pot until hot.

title: butterfly shrimp
directions: Cut shrimp lengthwise and spread.
Sprinkle with pepper and garlic salt.
Combine sherry and soy sauce in a small bowl.
Add shrimp; stir to coat.
Combine eggs, cornstarch and baking powder; stir until smooth.
Dip shrimp in egg batter.
Deep fry for 3 to 4 minutes on each side until brown.

title: hoppin john
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.
If not enough juice in peas, add a little water.
Can use jalapeno peas.

title: orange-coconut cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Set aside. Combine egg yolks and next 3 ingredients, then stir into sugar mixture.

title: banana orange bread(sugarless cooking)
directions: Sift dry ingredients; set aside.
Blend bananas, frozen orange juice and eggs.
Stir in flour mixture, raisins and nuts.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a 9 x 4-inch greased bread pan at 350° for 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mushroom barley and navy bean soup(makes 8 servings)
directions: Place all ingredients (except Tabasco) in a large 8-quart pot. Slowly bring to boil and simmer, covered, for 2 hours (if you are using soaked dried beans) or for 1 hour if you are using canned beans.
If the level of liquid goes down, replace it with water or the soup will end up being too thick.
Season to taste with Tabasco.
This soup keeps on improving with each reheating!

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and most of sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients.
Knead dough on floured board.
Place in bowl and chill.
Spread reserved sugar on rolled out dough and roll lightly before cutting out.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: summer slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, celery, red onion in a large bowl.
Mix vinegar, sugar, garlic, salt, mustard seed together to dissolve dry ingredients.
Pour over veggie mixture and stir well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
(One package of coleslaw mix may be used in place of cabbage.)
Other seasonings as preferred. Lasts several days.

title: cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter and press into 9 X 13 pan. Beat the chilled milk well, as for whipped cream, in a large bowl. Dissolve the jello in hot water. Mix cream cheese with sugar and vanilla. Add jello mixture, the add it all to the whipped milk. Pout into pan with crust. Place in refrigerator until set and ready to cut.

title: cheese broccoli dip
directions: Melt cheese (this can be done in microwave).
Add rest of ingredients and heat in crock-pot.

title: oniony oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub and wash potatoes; pat dry.
Cut into cubes.
Do not peel.
Toss in large mixing bowl with oil and soup mix.
Bake in 425° oven until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: greek spaghetti
directions: Saute olives, onion and green pepper.
Add mushroom soup and tomatoes.
Simmer until bubbly.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer spaghetti and sauce.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: lemon gelatin cake
directions: Combine cake mix, gelatin, oil and water.
Beat 4 minutes. Add eggs one at a time.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in angel food cake pan.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in small pieces.
Place in mixing bowl with 1 cup sugar, evaporated milk, milk, vanilla, egg yolks and butter.
Mix well.
Pour into 10 x 8 x 2-inch size baking pan.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove and make meringue.

title: honey roasted nuts
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil; grease foil.
Combine honey, oleo and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bring to boil.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put nuts in medium bowl.
Pour mixture over nuts.
Stir until evenly coated.
Spread on pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until nuts are glazed and lightly browned.
Do not allow nuts to burn.
Cool.
Combine sugar and remaining cinnamon; toss with glazed nuts to coat.
Makes 4 cups.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix and pour in jar.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square pan and bake 20 minutes at 425°.
(I melt 3 tablespoons of shortening in the pan I'm going to use and leave the extra grease in the pan.)

title: glorified chicken
directions: Brown chicken in shortening in skillet; pour off fat.
Stir in soup.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes or until done.
Stir often. Serves 4.

title: hornet cake
directions: Cook vanilla pudding as directed on box.
When it starts to boil, remove from heat.
Let cool 3 to 5 minutes.
In same kettle, pour yellow cake mix into pudding.
Beat with mixer for 5 minutes. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan sprayed with Pam.
Must be glass pan!
Sprinkle chips and nuts on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: favorite yellow cake
directions: Beat flour, sugar, Crisco, milk and vanilla with electric mixer for 3 minutes at high speed.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes at low speed.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans or a 9 x 13-inch oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350°.
Bake layers 30 to 35 minutes or oblong 40 to 45 minutes until cake tests done. Great with chocolate or coconut frosting.

title: ham and cheese soft tacos
directions: Place ham and cheese on top of flour tortilla, fold over and stick together with toothpick.
Microwave about 30 seconds on High.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook bacon and onion until crisp.
Drain.
Add bacon, onion and remaining ingredients to beans.
Bake, uncovered, in 1 1/2-quart casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bryan's stir-fry
directions: Mix soy sauce, 1 tablespoon olive oil, garlic and ginger.
Add beef to coat and marinate 1 hour.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken in the water.
Remove chicken; let cool.
Cook shells according to box directions.
Let shells cool.
Make your favorite stuffing mix.
Cut the chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix the cut up chicken in the already prepared stuffing.
Stuff the shells with the chicken stuffing mixture.
Place stuffed shells in a covered casserole dish.

title: shirred eggs
directions: Grease individual oven service ware dishes.
Break egg into dish.
Season with salt and black pepper.
Top with 1 teaspoon or more of cream.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for approximately 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Eggs should not be hard.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve hot with toast or biscuits.

title: 6 cans casserole
directions: Combine all six ingredients and bake, covered, 45 minutes at 350°.
(Keep ingredients together on hand and have ready for an emergency meal.)

title: majestic layered salad
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients in order listed in a 2-quart salad bowl.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and bring to a rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Set aside and stir in last 2 ingredients.
Pour on buttered pizza pan.
Cool and cut.

title: creole pie in scone shell
directions: Brown meat lightly in skillet. Add onion and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft but not brown. Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes. Cook until blended.
Stir until smooth and thickened. Add vegetables and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot scone shell.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine buttermilk and soda.
Combine flour and spices; add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in apple butter and pecans.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan.

title: hershey's kiss cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into balls about the size of walnuts.
Bake for about 10 minutes at 400°.
Remove from heat. Push a candy kiss in the center of each baked cookie.
Return to oven.
Bake for 2 more minutes.
You can use Hugs or Kisses in this recipe.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Ingredients can be doubled for larger crowds.
Put ingredients into double boiler.
Cook until thickens.
Can be thinned with water if you wish to store and heat later.
Good and creamy!

title: tuna chow mein
directions: Saute the celery, onion and green pepper in the butter.
Stir in the tuna fish (with liquid).
Add 1/2 can chow mein noodles, cream of mushroom soup, milk, water, pepper and peanuts.
Pour into ungreased casserole and sprinkle with remaining noodles. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: patch 'm up soup
directions: Brown ground beef in Teflon pan and drain in colander.
Place cooked meat in large pot.
Add the 2 cans of stewed tomatoes, the can of tomato sauce, the onion soup mix, 4 cups water and the sugar and frozen mixed vegetables.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 8 good servings.

title: black skillet pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add sugar mixture to butter.
In separate pan, combine egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook slowly.
Stir constantly.
Add this to skillet mixture.
Cook slow; stir constantly until thick and smooth.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top for meringue.

title: pear preserves
directions: In a large, heavy pot, combine pears, sugar, water and lemon. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat.
Cover and cook until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: cranberry stuffing for turkey or chicken
directions: Saute onion, garlic and celery in chicken broth until tender. In a large bowl, combine bread, crumbled bacon, sauteed onion mixture, cranberries, garlic salt, fresh ground pepper, herbs and spices and nuts.
Toss to combine.
Moisten with orange juice.
Add 2 eggs; toss to thoroughly combine.
Stuff into cavity of turkey, packing lightly, or spread stuffing in a baking pan prepared with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: shake and bake for chicken
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator.
This recipe is equal to 20 packages of Shake 'n Bake.

title: light fluffy pancakes
directions: Beat 2 eggs and buttermilk.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Fry until golden brown.

title: corn salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Just before serving, add 3 cups Fritos and toss.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread wax paper heavily with paprika.
Roll cheese in ball.
It will be soft.
Cover with paprika.
Wrap in wax paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve with crackers or warm slices of French bread.

title: easy chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; mix well.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is smooth; stir often.
Use as a dip for corn chips or as a topper for baked potatoes or fries.

title: quick and easy skillet chowder
directions: Heat garlic butter and oil in large skillet.
I like to use my electric skillet for this. Add the potatoes and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
This usually takes about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add corn, bacon, half & half, white pepper, paprika, salt and chives.
Continue cooking over low heat for about 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
If desired, sprinkle a little cheese over the top of each serving.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Add 1 tablespoon of vinegar to the sour milk.
Mix sugar, oil and margarine, beating until creamy.
Put soda in sour milk and add to oil mixture.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to the oil mixture.
Fold in zucchini and put into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: michigan rocks
directions: Cream butter.
Add brown sugar and cream mixture.
Add eggs. Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Then add dates and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes a small soft cookie.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and egg.
Add sifted flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on aluminum foil covered pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp. Cool on sheet for 2 minutes for both.
Makes about 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, except potatoes.
Add potatoes.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs or chips.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Serve hot.

title: vidalia onion pickles
directions: Sprinkle salt on chopped onions and cover with ice.
Let stand 2 1/2 hours (very important).
Squeeze onions out of salt and ice mixture. Mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery salt and mustard. Bring to boil.
Drop squeezed onions into vinegar mixture.
Heat and pack in sterile jars.

title: brown rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine until amber colored.
Add consomme, rice, bouillon cube and water.
Mix and pour into baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed on box in 2 layer cake pan. Mix pudding as directed on box.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken (don't salt).
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing; set aside.
Take 1 1/2 cans of broth from chicken; add soups and mix.
Then layer as follows in an ungreased casserole dish:
first layer stuffing, second layer chicken and third layer soup.
Repeat, ending with a layer of stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon cake
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Oil a Bundt pan; sprinkle flour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Let cake stand in pan.

title: walnut cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla. Beat on low speed just until combined. Stir in the walnuts. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9 x 1/2-inch round cake pans. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes; remove from pans to a wire rack to cool completely. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting. Store in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: In saucepan bring sugar and syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix sausage, cheese and biscuit mix until blended. Shape into walnut size balls.
Place on a rack in a shallow pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve hot with mustard or freeze for later use.
Makes 48 puffs.

title: philadelphia's barrel pickles
directions: Cover to rim with boiling water.
Cover and let stand on kitchen counter at least 24 hours!
Refrigerate and indulge in several days.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and cocoa.
Heat until butter melts; boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add vanilla and quick oats.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: vanilla cream pudding
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch and salt in a 2-quart saucepan. Combine milk and egg yolks.
Stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
After mixture thickens, boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in margarine and vanilla.

title: cream of taco
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix browned beef,
Ro-tel tomatoes, whipping cream, chile, beans and velveeta all together in a crock pot and cook for 45 minutes on high, then cook for a couple of hours on low.
Crumble tortilla chips on plate and top with cream mixture,
Add chopped tomatoes, lettuce, grated cheese, black olives and sour cream if desired.

title: lemon-blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs and yogurt until smooth.
Add thawed blueberries.
Bake in greased, floured angel food or Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broiled chuck supreme
directions: Pierce both sides of steak, or steaks, well with fork.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine tomato sauce, vinegar, horseradish, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour over steak.
Refrigerate overnight. Broil steak to desired doneness.
If desired, simmer remaining marinade in saucepan 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add a little marinade to the sour cream, then fold the sour cream into marinade.
Heat slowly.
Serve over steak.

title: quick vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and flavorings; mix.
Measure flour, stir dry ingredients together and blend together. Refrigerate 1 to 3 hours.
Place on greased cookie sheet by teaspoons full.
Makes 5 dozen.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and add to stuffing mix.
Cook squash and onions together.
Drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients to the squash.
In casserole dish, put 1/2 of stuffing in bottom, then all of the squash mixture, then remaining 1/2 of the stuffing over top.
Bake at 350°
for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: tangy german potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes; cover with water and boil until done, not firm (use boiling not baking potatoes).
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and save 3 tablespoons drippings and crumble bacon.
Saute onion and celery.
Add flour, sugar, water, vinegar, salt and pepper. Cook until mixture thickens.
Slice potatoes and bacon; place in a large bowl, adding some sauce mixture to coat.
Serve hot or at room temperature.

title: mexican chef salad
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add kidney beans and salt. Simmer while preparing rest of salad.
Chop lettuce and tomatoes. Toss with Thousand Island dressing and grated Cheddar cheese. Crunch and add taco chips.
Drain ground beef mixture, and add to rest of salad.
Serve pronto!

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together and chill.

title: chocolate torte
directions: First Step:
Combine
plain flour, oleo and 1 cup nuts. Press into pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.	Bake at 350°.
Cool.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown onion with ground beef.
In large soup pot add remaining ingredients.
Heat together and simmer 15 minutes.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Press mixture firmly and evenly into lightly buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over mixture.
Chill at least one hour. Cut into 2-inch pieces.

title: onioned potatoes
directions: Wrap mixture in 2 layers of foil and grill about 20 minutes.

title: quick surprise dessert
directions: Mix cookies and cream cheese together.
Follow directions on box to prepare pudding.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain well. Saute onion in oleo margarine, add herb dressing, stir in corn, broccoli, and eggs. Add seasonings. Pour into 3 quart casserole (I use a 9 x 13-inch pan).

title: curried chicken salad with mango and cashews
directions: In a large bowl, toss together the chicken, lemon juice and the mangoes.
Add the celery and the scallions.
In a small bowl whisk together the yogurt, mayonnaise, curry powder and cumin and add the dressing to the chicken mixture with salt and pepper to taste. Combine the salad well.

title: graham cracker crunches
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Place a layer of graham crackers on foil.
Put brown sugar and butter in pan and bring to boil. Boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over crackers and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream margarine and shortening until smooth.
Add vanilla. Beat in confectioners sugar gradually.
Beat in flour gradually. Use hands to mix in pecans which have been chopped or broken coarsely.
Roll in cocoon shapes and bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 15 to 20 minutes until light brown at 350°.
Roll in confectioners sugar just before serving.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: In saucepan, mix together sugar and corn starch.
Add butter and salt, and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, adding milk slowly, until thick.
Pour into a pre-baked, cooled pie shell. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put in a pre-heated 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: veggie quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix half and half and eggs; set aside. In skillet, saute vegetables and garlic in olive oil until tender. Add herbs, salt and pepper.
Add to the egg mixture and pour into preheated pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until nearly set.
Top with shredded Mozzarella cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes more.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and butter together.
Blend in milk and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: cheesey potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: irish lamb stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 5 or 6-quart Dutch oven, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp, about 10 minutes.
Remove bacon; drain off and discard fat.

title: pastry cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients together and chill for 2 to 4 hours. Roll into 1-inch balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Remove promptly and cool on rack.

title: vivian's poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over broccoli mixture. Marinate several hours before serving. Toss several times while chilling.

title: pineapple-cool whip salad
directions: Warm pineapple with juice; mix with jello.
Cool and add Cool Whip and cottage cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Set broccoli out to thaw. Melt butter. Add onion, flour, salt and water. Stir until smooth. Add Cheez Whiz and eggs. Stir until sauce forms. Mix 1/4 cup cracker crumbs and broccoli. Pour sauce over broccoli. Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve with fresh vegetable sticks.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli by directions and add remaining ingredients. Pour into a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone and dice.
Heat Ro-Tel, onion soup and broth together.
Layer corn tortillas on bottom of casserole dish with no holes.
Put 1/2 chicken and 1/2 broth mixture over tortillas; layer with cheese.
Repeat layers, topping with cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°, or until hot and bubbly all the way through.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Put broccoli in boiling water in bite-size pieces.
When comes to second boil, remove and drain, then chill.
Mix and chill. Serve with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili rellenos dip(salsa)
directions: Mix and chill.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: low-fat fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla flavoring.
Add drained fruit and grapes.
Mix well.
Then sprinkle dry pudding on this and stir well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: praline sauce
directions: Boil water.
Add pecans.
Reduce heat and cook 5 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Combine sugar, syrup and margarine.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in pecans.

title: fresh cream of mushroom soup
directions: Clean mushrooms; chop stems finely and caps medium fine.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Saute onion until soft; add chopped mushrooms.
Cook lightly 2 minutes; add chicken stock.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Microwave white sauce with rest of margarine, flour, milk and cream.
Stir into mushroom mixture.
Add seasonings and sherry.

title: tostada casserole
directions: Fry meat; drain.
Add beans, onion, salsa, seasoning and pepper.
Crush chips; put in a layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top.
Put in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; crush a few more chips on top.
Put cheese on top; bake 5 minutes more.

title: pepperoni and cheese bread
directions: *Quantities depend on personal preferences and quantity of dough being used.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples, remove stems.
Insert a wooden skewer into the stem end of each apple.
In a heavy 3-quart saucepan melt butter.
Stir in sugar, corn syrup and dash of salt; mix well.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients setting aside 1 cup of pecans.
Shape into ball.
Roll in pecans.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers.

title: grandmother myers' shortcake
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar together.
Add baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Alternate flour and milk until mixed.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into 12-inch pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain.
In a buttered casserole dish, layer broccoli and sliced Velveeta cheese.
Top the last layer with crushed Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Take all the above ingredients and mix together very well. Form into the shape of a small football. Put into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish or pan. Then spread on top the following mixture: 1 teaspoon mustard and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: gorditas
directions: Add flour to corn meal in a large bowl.
Add boiling water to dry ingredients (enough to form a stiff dough).
Shape dough around small chunks of cheese.
Shape like a biscuit.
Drop in hot grease; cook until firm or lightly brown.
Cool slightly. Slit open and add sauce.

title: nacho dabs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Set aside 6 1/2 dozen whole tortilla chips; use no broken ones.
Place chips on cookie sheet individually.
Top each with 1 teaspoon beans, some cheese and a jalapeno pepper ring.
Bake at 400° for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together.
Cook and stir over medium heat.
Will thicken. Add food color sparingly, if desired.

title: coconut pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix eggs, margarine and pineapple juice together.
Then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: roy rogers' favorite butterscotch pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Beat egg yolks.
Stir in some of the hot mixture, then return all to saucepan and cook, stirring 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until butter melts.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with meringue or whipped cream.

title: baked hawaiian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken, skin side up, in a shallow greased baking dish.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in green pepper, pineapple, mustard and honey.
Spoon mixture over chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400°, basting occasionally, 45 to 60 minutes, until tender.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let set for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: taggart's you have to try hard to mess this up chocolate candy
directions: Melt the margarine in a large saucepan.
Pour in the milk and sugar.
Mix well.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 8 to 9 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Add the chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Stir until the chocolate and marshmallow is completely melted and mixed.
Pour into a buttered dish and let cool before cutting.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugars, butter, oil and eggs until light and creamy.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together and gradually add to creamed mixture.
Drop by small balls on greased cookie sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: beef balls
directions: Mix ground beef, soup mix, oatmeal and eggs and form into small balls.
Place in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, turning to brown evenly.
Cook remaining ingredients and pour over beef balls.
May be cooked in a slow oven for 2 to 3 hours, may be placed in slow cooker and covered with gravy mixture.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill for several hours so flavors can blend.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 6 cups of salsa.

title: pumpkin cookie bars
directions: Combine flour, oats, nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add butter; mix until crumbly.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove.
Reduce oven heat to 325°.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a bowl and divide in half. Scramble eggs and add milk.
Slowly add half of dry ingredients and blend together.
Roll mushroom slices in wet mixture, then in dry mixture.
Shake off excess and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with salt.
Serve immediately.

title: sausage stuffing broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions. Drain.
In skillet over medium heat, cook sausage until browned.
Remove fat.
In a large bowl, combine cooked sausage, cooked broccoli, croutons and cheese. Toss lightly to mix. Arrange mixture evenly in greased baking dish.
In the same bowl, stir soup until smooth. Beat in eggs and milk. Pour over sausage mixture, covering all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until set in center.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Cut in squares.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients until almost done.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: sweet and sour swiss chard
directions: Place chard in a large bowl; set aside.
Cook turkey bacon until crisp.
Drain, crumble and set aside.
In same skillet, cook onion until tender, but not brown.
Blend in sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook until thick and bubbly. Pour the hot mixture over the chard, tossing to coat.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chicken salad sandwiches
directions: On microwave-cooking rack, arrange 12 very thin unpeeled potato slices in circle; sprinkle with salt.
Cook on High 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, until brown.
Rotate rack half way through cooking.
Let stand 1 minute.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Cook all other ingredients in saucepan until thickened.
Combine with cheese.
Serve.

title: puntas de filete (mexican beef tips)
directions: Rub the ingredients into the beef strips and refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown first two ingredients and drain.
Add soup and salsa. Let simmer about 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, lay 1/2 bag of chips.
Top with half of hamburger mixture and cheese.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in an 11 x 8-inch dish. Combine remaining ingredients except paprika, including mushroom liquid.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach-maple syrup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve on waffles, pancakes or hot cereal.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple; mix with pudding.
After it's mixed, add to Cool Whip; mix well.
Add nuts if you like for additional flavor.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl, combine apple cider, ReaLemon and sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Garnish with apple slices or cinnamon sticks, if desired.
Serve over ice.
Yields about 3
quarts.

title: sour cream ice cream
directions: Combine sour cream and sweetened milk in freezer container. Add whole milk.
Add fruit and stir.
Add vanilla to taste. Freeze in electric freezer.
Can use peaches, strawberries, etc. in place of pineapple.

title: gnocchi
directions: Mix the ingredients to form a ball.
Roll the dough into 6-inch lengths.
Press roll with finger to make small indentations.
Cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in boiling water until gnocchi comes to top, then boil for 1 more minute.
Drain and serve with spaghetti sauce and cheese.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo. Add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sliced cucumbers
directions: Mix altogether; let stand an hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Let rise. Punch down. Form into loaves. Let rise and bake at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together; chill and serve.

title: pineapple fluff
directions: Combine milk and marshmallows.
Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Cool.
Drain pineapple, whip the cream and then add drained pineapple and whipped cream to marshmallow mixture.
Put graham cracker crumbs in cake pan and pour the prepared mixture over crumbs.
Top this with more crumbs.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: homestyle "boursin"
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Use as spread on pita triangles, or dip for veggies.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix sugar, milk and cinnamon.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add vanilla.
Pour in nuts and stir to coat.
Dump on waxed paper. Separate pecans on waxed paper and let dry.

title: chicken 'n dressing, mother's day out
directions: Mix
beaten
eggs
and
milk;
pour
evenly
over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out one hour before baking and spread with one can mushroom soup. Bake, uncovered,
about
40 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: braised winter vegetables with thyme
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat butter or oil over medium heat.
Add shallots and saute for 2 minutes, or until softened. Add leeks, carrots, parsnips and celery and saute for 1 minute. Sprinkle with thyme, then stir in wine and stock.
Reduce heat to low; cover the pan tightly and simmer until the vegetables are tender, 7 to 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and serve immediately.
Serves 4.
Per serving:
31 calories and 1 gram fat.

title: crouton chicken casserole
directions: Mix water, margarine and croutons together.
In a buttered casserole dish, put 3/4 crouton mixture on the bottom.
Layer green beans, chicken and rest of the crouton mixture.
Put soups and liquid over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix and bake the biscuits as you normally do when using prepared mix substituting beer for liquid and add sugar.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Microwave Preparation:
Wash and dry mushrooms; remove and chop stems.
In large glass bowl, combine bacon, green pepper and onion.
Cover with paper towels and cook on High (max) 4 minutes, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Add cream cheese, Worcestershire and mushroom stems.
Mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with bacon mixture.

title: memphis peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and peanut butter.
Set aside 1/3 of mixture. Spread remaining 2/3 over bottom of baked crust.

title: chocolate chip meringue bars
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda; set aside.
Combine and beat until light shortening, sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add vanilla, water and beaten egg yolks.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
