Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Beat 2 egg whites until frothy. Gradually add 1/2 cup brown sugar; blend until sugar is dissolved. Spread over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, then peanut butter. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pickled hot peppers by the pint
directions: In non-aluminum saucepan, heat vinegar and water for each pint of peppers.
Into each sterilized pint jar, place 1 clove garlic, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed, 1/2 teaspoon of pickling salt and 2 cups hot peppers.
Leave 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles. Seal.
Process BWB for 5 minutes.
Adjust seals.
Cool untouched for 12 hours.

title: donna's casserole
directions: Brown beef (scrambled); sprinkle with chili powder while cooking.
Layer the ground beef, potatoes and onion in order given in 2 or 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Repeat layers, if desired.
Pour over all, the mushroom soup, tomato soup and milk.
Sprinkle with herb stuffing mix and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake covered in 375° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spaghetti casserole(makes 4 servings)
directions: Mix these together; spoon over spaghetti mixture.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 20 minutes).

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat
flour,
butter,
sugar
and
salt
until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Press firmly into prepared dish. Bake 20
to 23 minutes or until golden brown.
Top with filling and finish baking as directed following.

title: toffee
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line jelly roll pan with foil. Place graham crackers in pan in single layer.
Combine brown sugar with margarine, bring to boil and pour over graham crackers. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes and sprinkle chocolate chips on top of crackers. Let chips melt and spread them around. Sprinkle nuts on top of chocolate. Cool completely and break into pieces.

title: 24 carat cake
directions: Lightly mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat 1 minute at medium.
Stir in carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
Turn into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round pans or a large rectangular pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and finish cooling.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and lemon-colored; add oil, carrots and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Next, add pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Mix and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: orange baked pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops or steaks.
Place in shallow baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Baste occasionally.
Can also be put in crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake cake; pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Let cool, then pour cream of coconut.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Top with coconut. Keep in refrigerator.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt. Gradually add scalded milk.
Add rice, raisins, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole. Set in shallow pan and pour hot water into pan 1-inch deep.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Cut cheese into cubes in bowl. Strain cooked macaroni; pour into cheese.
Stir while hot.
Add milk and eggs (beat milk and eggs with dash of salt and pepper) and stir together.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix cheese, flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine and mix together.
Make into a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill overnight.
Slice thin and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sack
directions: Thaw pastry for 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
On a floured surface or between two sheets of waxed paper, roll the sheet of puff pastry into a 14-inch square.
In the center of the sheet, place chocolate chips, walnuts and butter.
Pull pastry edges together.
Twist and turn the ends together to seal "package".
Smooth folds in dough.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Let stand 10 minutes at least before cutting.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican party wings
directions: Blend Ranch dressing and chilies.
Refrigerate while preparing drummies.
Mix flour and taco mix together.
Add oil, stir till well combined.
Coat drummies with flour mixture.
Coat again.
Put on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn and bake another 20 to 25 minutes.
Longer if needed.
Serve with ranch dressing mixture.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Clean and devein shrimp.
Chop large shrimp in half or fourths (bite-sized pieces).
Set shrimp aside.

title: coconut pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Stir gelatin into 1/4 cup water.
Combine next 9 ingredients in top of a double boiler and cook 10 minutes over boiling water, stirring constantly.
Stir into softened gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat 1 egg white until foamy.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar and continue beating until stiff.
Fold into pumpkin mixture with vanilla and toasted coconut (to toast coconut, spread in shallow pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes, stirring once or twice).
Turn into baked pie shell.
Chill.
Garnish with whipped cream and coconut.

title: chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Melt margarine with chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Beat in the evaporated milk.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.
Return to heat; cook until desired thickness.
Great over pound cake or ice cream.

title: zucchini and meat balls
directions: In a large skillet together cook zucchini and meat balls.
Add green peppers and chopped onion; season to taste.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: beef jerky
directions: Leave beef roast or steak partially chilled to make it easier to cut.
Slice into thin strips and weigh up about 3 pounds. Marinate overnight in mixture of all ingredients and put in dehydrator the next day.
If you don't have a dehydrator, you can take shish kabob sticks and hang the strips in the oven at 250° for about 6 hours.

title: hearty breakfast skillet
directions: Brown sausage in large nonstick skillet on medium heat; drain. Add potatoes and tomatoes; cook 5 minutes. Top with Velveeta cheese. Beat eggs. Pour evenly over the ingredients in the skillet; cover. Reduce heat to low. Cook until egg mixture is set in center and cheese is melted. Uncover and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese with margarine.
Blend and add flour; chill for 15 minutes.
Shape into crust in bottom of tart pans.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients to flour, mixing well, then add rhubarb.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Cover with topping made from nuts, white sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: no bake reese's cups
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Press into a 10 x 16-inch pan.
Then melt 16 ounces of chocolate and spread over top of first mixture.
Let mixtures cool.
Cut in squares and eat.

title: clear vegetable soup(20 minutes stove to table)
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over high heat, heat chicken, broth, water, carrot and celery to boiling.
Add rotelle.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer until macaroni is done, about 20 minutes. Ladle soup into bowls.
Top with parsley.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
In a saucepan, bring to a boil the shortening, water, margarine and cocoa.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture while hot and beat with mixer.
Add buttermilk, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Blend together good and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cabbage on the grill
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
On the bottom, cut a little off so it sits flat.
Cut out the core so you have a little hole.
Set 1/2 stick of butter in each hole and sprinkle seasoning salt over and pepper.
Wrap up in tinfoil.
Cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours; don't turn.

title: creamy butter frosting
directions: In a small mixer bowl beat butter until light and fluffy. Gradually add about half of the powdered sugar, beating well. Beat in the egg and vanilla.
Gradually beat in remaining powdered sugar, then add milk if necessary to make frosting of spreading consistency.
Frost top of cake and sides.

title: old fashion rhubarb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Stir in rhubarb.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: slim brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 brownies, 95 calories per brownie.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cover with water and cook until tender. While beans are boiling, add onion, bell pepper and sausage.
Add garlic and salt and pepper.
If you want it hotter, add Tabasco sauce.
Serve over rice.

title: impossible ham and broccoli pie
directions: Chop ham, add onion, salt, pepper. Layer on bottom of 13 x 9 inch pan, the cottage cheese and Parmesan. Next layer the broccoli, ham, onions, salt and pepper. Top with half the cheese. Beat milk, baking mix and eggs. Pour over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cheese straws
directions: Blend together well.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, oil and eggs; pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; before baking, take cherry pie filling and spoon onto 16 spots on unbaked cake (4 tablespoons in each direction).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
To serve, cut loose from pan, cut in square, turn upside down on serving plates.
Top with Cool Whip or powdered sugar.

title: italian potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes long way (wedge shape) as many as you need for the meal.
Sprinkle garlic, oregano, basil, parsley and red pepper over top.
Slice onion over top and Italian seasoning.
Add sliced butter over top.
Place in 500° oven, turn often and cook about 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Line 24 muffin cups with paper or foil baking cups. Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.

In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, nutmeg, vanilla, and eggs at medium speed, scraping sides of bowl occasionally. Pour mixture into prepared muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Bake at 325° for 20-25 minutes or until set. Meanwhile, melt preserves in small saucepan over low heat. Carefully spoon 1 tsp. melted preserves over top.
Cover pan; refrigerate over night. Before serving, remove paper baking cups and bring to room temperature. *Cheesecakes can be made up to 1 month ahead and frozen.
Garnish with preserves 1 day before serving and let thaw in refrigerator. This is a good make-ahead recipe.

title: beans and things
directions: Combine all ingredients; place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until it begins to bubble and brown at the edges.
This dish can be made ahead and refrigerated, but add about 15 minutes baking time.
Great for covered dish dinners as it holds its heat and may be rewarmed.

title: cheesy snack mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place pretzels in large bowl.
In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over pretzels; stir until well coated.
Transfer to 2 ungreased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely on baking sheets.
Store in an airtight container.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving 1/2 cup nuts. Chill completely. Form a ball and roll in remaining nuts.

title: buttered hot and sweet nibbles
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In a large bowl, combine pretzels and crackers; set aside.
In a small saucepan, melt butter; add chili powder and sugar and cook and stir for one minute.
Pour over pretzels and crackers and toss to coat.
On an ungreased shallow baking pan, spread mixture in a single layer.
Bake until dry
and golden, about 15 minutes, stirring once.
Cool completely.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: chocolate spectacular
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and 3/4 cup nuts.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; then cool.

title: nutty apple muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in apples, nuts and coconut.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 18 muffins.

title: country pot roast
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt and pepper.
Coat roast.
In hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat, brown roast on all sides. Add onion, celery and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add tomato juice, 1/4 cup water, Worcestershire and oregano.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours, turning meat once.
Add carrots; simmer 30 minutes or until carrots are tender. Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.

title: apple fritters
directions: Add all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Spoon in with a large spoon into hot grease.
Let brown and remove and drain. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crumb cake
directions: Pour in tin and sprinkle crumbs over the top.
Use a flat tin about 1 1/2-inch deep and 7 x 10 x 1 1/2-inch or little larger. Bake at 350°.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400 F. Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar, shortening and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Beat into sugar mixture, stir in walnuts.
Chill 30 minutes. Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cookies.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; add pineapple.	Add flour, baking powder, salt, soda, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a bread loaf pan and top with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix this together. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.	Makes 1 loaf.

title: pizza pie dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water with sugar.
Mix rest of ingredients. Let rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Push dough into pizza pan.
Makes 3 medium pizzas.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not make dough too stiff.

title: nut brown buttermilk bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; beat egg and add sugar.
Mix well; stir in butter and buttermilk.
Blend into dry ingredients quickly just until moistened.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: grandma's risotto
directions: Brown onion in butter; add rice and two beef bouillon cubes. Add chicken base.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add water alternately until rice is cooked.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, soak bread in milk 5 minutes.
Add sugar, butter, salt, eggs and vanilla; mix well. Stir in pecans.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water in oven.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: sugar bear squares
directions: Melt margarine.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cereal and peanuts; toss to coat well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.

title: pan fried cabbage and meat
directions: Brown beef and	onions,
slice	cabbage
into
mixture. Cover and cook over medium
heat	until cabbage is done.	Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana spice pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch or Bundt tube pan.
Whip egg whites until foamy.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1 cup sugar gradually, beating until peaks form.
In another bowl, cream together butter and remaining sugar.
Beat in yolks gradually.
Add orange juice. Combine flour, baking powder, remaining salt and cardamom.
Add to butter mixture alternately with mashed bananas.

title: fantastic cake
directions: Stir ingredients together until well blended.
No need to beat with mixer.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Slice pickles, drain and put in a big container.
Add sugar, garlic cloves and Tabasco sauce and seal in a large jar. Refrigerate. Reverse jar top to bottom each day for two weeks; leave as turned (upside down) daily.

title: beef goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion. Add soup, beans, chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer for 1 hour.
Thicken with flour and water mixture. Serve over rice.

title: crabmeat quiche
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add crabmeat; stir on low heat.
Let cool.
Stir other ingredients together.
Add sauteed mixture, then add cheese and stir.
Pour in single pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions together.
Pour boiling water over peppers, and let stand until cool.
Drain, put in boiling vinegar mixture and cook 15 minutes.
Cool and pack in jars (be sure to put in sealed jars).

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add 2 packs taco seasoning (follow package directions).
In large bowl combine lettuce, tomato, olives, cheese, onion and Doritos.
When taco meat is done, add to the bowl.
Pour French dressing and mix.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake according to directions.
Let cool. Split layers when completely cool.
Mix sour cream, sugar and flavoring.
Save 1/2 cup of mixture for icing.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook wild rice.
Crumble sausage in frying pan and cook until done.
Mix together with can of mushroom soup.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice and	milk
in covered pan on low heat.
Cook together until milk
is absorbed into rice, about 1 1/2 hours. Stir occasionally.	Remove pan from heat.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla; stir in
cream.
Pour this mixture into pan with rice and place back on
stove.
Bring
to
a
boil
over
low heat, stirring
constantly.
Pour
into
x
9-inch
glass
dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg,
immediately.
Cover with Saran Wrap and chill.
You may add
cup drained crushed pineapple or 1 cup of raisins.

title: frittatas
directions: *Could also use packaged stir-fry vegetables.

title: quick chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in skillet over high heat. Cut chicken into strips. Add to skillet with garlic. Stir-fry for 3 minutes. Add vegetables. Stir-fry an additional 3 minutes. Reduce heat to medium. Stir in mayo, soy sauce and ginger. Simmer for 1 minute. Serve over rice.

title: carrot-orange cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat butter, sugar and eggs in a large bowl at high speed for 3 minutes. Add flour alternately with juice, starting and ending with flour. Stir in rind, carrots and walnuts.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until top springs back when pressed. Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Wash peppers; remove tops and seeds.
Place upright in 2-quart microproof casserole.
Pour water over bottom of dish and cook, covered, on High (Max power) 2 minutes.
Drain water.
Let peppers stand while preparing filling.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, one at a time.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube pan.
Yields one 10-inch tube cake.
A good cake for cold weather with coffee. Very moist and spicy.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dash top with nutmeg.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes, then at 425° for 10 to 20 minutes, until filling is set.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and baking soda.

title: baked onions
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion rings in butter over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes, until tender.
Arrange onions in greased 12 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Blend soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Pour over cheese and onions and mix lightly.
Arrange buttered bread slices over top. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco delight
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a large skillet, about 5 minutes.
Add salsa, tomato sauce and bouillon cube.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover; remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Fluffy with a fork.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream, grated cheese, avocado and tortilla chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: new england baked beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight.
Drain.
Pour into baking pan with seasonings, onion, maple syrup, cider vinegar and salt pork. Cover and bake in 300° oven 6 hours.
Uncover last half hour to brown beans.

title: karen's 3 bean hot salad
directions: Drain onions and bacon.
Crumble bacon.
Mix all.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground meat and garlic powder until done, about 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini mexicali
directions: Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Add sliced zucchini, carrot, onion, celery, green pepper strips, garlic salt, basil and pepper; toss to mix well.
Cook, covered, over medium-high heat for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine picante sauce and mustard.
Stir into vegetables.
Add tomato wedges.
Cook uncovered 3 to 5 minutes or until heated through.
Season with salt.
Serve in skillet or transfer to serving dish.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Use either a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer cake pans.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: grandma's molasses feather cake
directions: Heat oven to 375° (moderate).
Use one-bowl method.
Sift first 5 ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening, molasses, eggs, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Mix until all flour is dampened.
Beat 2 minutes by hand or electric beater (low speed). Add milk.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Bake 25 minutes or until done in 2 well-greased, lightly floured, round 8-inch layer cake pans. Cool; frost as desired.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased pan.
Cook at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: holiday cherry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add graham cracker crumbs and sugar.
Stir well and press flat in pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in the order listed. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Refrigerate before cutting.
Chill thoroughly.

title: great hot dog chili
directions: Brain beef and drain fat.
Mix all ingredients together and cook on low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 pound.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Salt chicken to taste.
Place chicken and rice in a large baking dish.
Mix the cans of water and onion soup.
Pour over chicken and rice; cover with lid or foil.
Place in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake for 2 hours.

title: yummy chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in a large baking dish.
Mix 2 soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Cover with stuffing mix.
Cut margarine in pieces over top.
Pour cup of broth over all.
Serve with vegetables, cranberry sauce and salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg, then pour over apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; pour butter over top.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until it looks set on top and brown.

title: carrot drop cookies
directions: Cream together the egg, butter, sugar, mashed carrots and vanilla.
Blend in the dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water to 240°.
Add peanuts.
Cook to 295°, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter.
Stir until dissolved.
Add soda and salt; stir vigorously.
Pour out on a buttered slab and spread as thinly as possible.
Cool.
Break or cut into pieces when ready.
Makes about 50 pieces.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Form into 60 bite sized meatballs.
Place in shallow baking pan or jellyroll pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.
In a small saucepan, combine chili sauce and grape jelly.
Heat until jelly is melted.
Place well drained meatballs in serving dish.
Pour chili sauce mixture over. Stir gently to coat.
Serve warm.

title: turkey chili pot pie
directions: Cook turkey over medium heat with onion and garlic.
Stir in chili powder, tomatoes, water, salt, pepper and beans.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes on high.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with the biscuit and top with cheese.
Bake at 350°.

title: egg spinach salad
directions: Wash and drain spinach.
Transfer to large bowl and chill. In separate bowl, combine oil, sugar, vinegar, onion, salt and mustard.
Beat the dressing or mix in blender until it becomes thick and syrupy.
Tear spinach and add bacon and chopped eggs. Pour dressing over salad.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Toss the salad to mix it and garnish with egg slices.

title: broccoli-cauliflower dish
directions: Place cooked vegetables into casserole dish.
Combine mushroom soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and cheese.
Spread mixture over vegetables, then sprinkle with cheese crackers and almonds.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix flour and pecans together. Melt margarine and pour into flour.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Press in the bottom of a large Pyrex baking dish. Bake at 350° until brown (45 minutes). Cool.

title: mulled berry cider
directions: Tie spices
together
in
cheesecloth,
leaving
a good length of string
on the end.
Pour cider/cranberry juice into large pot. Add
cheesecloth
spice bag; let extra string hang over the pot. Bring
to a boil slowly, then reduce to simmer, keeping
pot partially
covered.
Ladle
out
all
afternoon. Yields 24 cups. Great at Christmas!

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Mix flour and salt in small bowl. Beat butter in bowl till smooth and creamy. Add sugar 1/2 c. at a time. Beat till fluffy. Beat in vanilla; add eggs one at a time stirring after each one. Stir flour mixture into butter mixture. Stir in buttermilk. Sprinkle pecans on bottom of piecrust. Pour in filling. Bake at 350 degree oven for 1 1/2 hours or until set.

title: pimento cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and parboil, then chill.
Grate as for hash browns.
Saute onions in butter.
Layer potatoes, onions, butter, pimentos and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate several hours before serving. Chill overnight, if possible.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine broth, tomatoes (with liquid), 1 cup of water, tabasco sauce, garlic, cumin and chili powder in a soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook uncovered 5 minutes.
Stir in cilantro, green onions and lime juice.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Mix together and spread on cookie sheet and toast. Stir often or it will burn. Put coconut mixture on top of pies. Pour 12 ounce jar of caramel sauce on top of coconut mixture. Freeze before trying to cut pie.

title: vera's chocolate cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs beaten, melted chocolate, sifted flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add vanilla and milk.
Bake at 325° in a square pan.

title: 7 day salad
directions: In a big bowl, combine all ingredients.
Add bacon bits and Ranch dressing or your favorite dressing.

title: plum sauce for dipping
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the soy sauce, in a pan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until plums
are
soft.
Stir in soy sauce.
Cool slightly and pour into your
blender.
Blend until smooth.
Refrigerate if not using immediately.
Will keep up to 1 week.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook steak in thin strips and brown slowly in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
When tender, add cream cheese and milk.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve on hot noodles.

title: foil chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, catsup, sugar, garlic and salt.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Wrap each piece of chicken in foil, adding 1 teaspoon of marinade to each piece.
Put on cookie sheet and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Break up the bread.
Put the chicken on top of bread.
Mix the softened oleo, eggs, salad dressing, milk, chicken broth and salt; put mixture on top of chicken and bread.
Put the cheese slices on top, then the soups.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Good with diced potatoes and peas.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in graham cracker crust. Chill for one hour.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding 7-Up last.
Serve over ice.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop green onions; add to broccoli and raisins.
*You may also use cauliflower.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli; use only florets.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over broccoli and cauliflower. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken madra
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in melted butter. Remove chicken.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add flour and curry powder.
Stir until smooth and bubbly (about 2 minutes). Stir in broth.
Bring to a boil; add chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 to 40 minutes.
If sauce is too thick, add more butter.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers into 2 halves.
Clean insides and rinse.
Boil rice until it's done.
Brown meat; add spices to meat (or spaghetti sauce).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix rice with meat; stuff meat and rice into shell.
Place stuffed shells in baking dishes.
Bake for 1 hour.
Take out of oven.
Add cheese on top. Place in oven until melted.

title: smoked salmon asparagus quiche
directions: Place pastry in quiche dish. Spread shredded (chunky) salmon, asparagus, onion, and half of the cheese in dish. In a large bowl beat eggs add creams and milk, salt (optional) pepper, mix well. Pour over items in dish, cover with remaining cheese. Bake in oven at 350 degrees until knife comes out the center clean.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix lightly.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and add eggs to mixture.
Mix and blend.
Add nuts and stir.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: irene's pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs. Mix flour, cinnamon, ginger, baking soda and powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add pumpkin, vanilla and lemon. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes.

title: trail blazer stew
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add rest of ingredients and simmer over fire. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Boil all ingredients for 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except crust.
Use the electric mixer and whip on high for 2 minutes.
Place in unbaked crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes or until when knife is inserted in the middle, comes out clean. Cool.

title: no bake fruity cereal squares
directions: In large saucepan heat margarine, corn syrup and dry gelatin. Boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly, remove from heat and stir in cereal with buttered spoon.
Pat mixture evenly into 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover and chill about 30 minutes. Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: grand's old-fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Beat ingredients by hand.
Pour into a pie shell; sprinkle top with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt.
Add milk, vanilla, eggs and margarine.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more. Good with vanilla wafers mixed in.
Cool before serving.

title: rev. doggett's apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Peel, core and slice apples. Pour mixture over prepared apples and toss to coat well.
Add orange juice and oleo.
Mix lightly.
Fill one of the pie shells with the apple mixture and use the other to lattice the top of the pie.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; lower oven temperature to 325° and bake for 45 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: date loaf
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Add dates; stir constantly until it makes a firm ball when tested in water.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour on buttered plate or roll in wet towel until hard, then slice.

title: chicken mayonnaise
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling stock.
When cool, add mayonnaise to stock.
Mix remaining ingredients with mayonnaise mixture. Pour in large casserole dish and refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: whipped icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Cool.
Mix sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Mix with a mixer; add cooled flour mixture a little at a time.
Mix well.
Makes enough icing for a 2 layer cake.

title: rolls
directions: Mix warm water with yeast.
Mix ingredients and drop in greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° until browned.
Yields 2 dozen muffins.

title: frozen strawberry yum-yum
directions: Mix flour, butter, brown sugar and nuts until crumbly, then press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool; break into crumbs.
Set aside.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl, add margarine, stir slightly.
Blend egg with milk, add to mixture in bowl.
Stir well with wooden spoon.
Add blueberries with spatula.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full (cupcake papers can be used).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All.
Mix other ingredients into Veg-All.
Pour into 1 1/2 quart greased casserole dish.
Bake until bubbly at 400°. Top with 20 Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and spoon around over Ritz.
Put back in oven for about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
You may garnish with additional grated cheese.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain orange and pineapple. Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soup and Ro-Tel in pan with 1/2 cup chicken broth from chicken.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Begin with Doritos, Velveeta, chicken and soup mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irene's hot dog meat sauce
directions: Saute oil, onion, chopped garlic clove, hamburg and mashed liverwurst in a large pot.
Add tomatoes, salt, chili powder, cloves, poultry seasoning and water; simmer 1 to 2 hours. you saute.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine or butter.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and coconut; mix.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and cook at 325° until done and firm.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Grind orange (including peel) and raisins together.
Beat well all other ingredients.
Add orange and raisins.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 325° until done.

title: chocolate rum angel
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler and cook over simmering water, stirring, until custard consistency and coats spoon (10 to 15 minutes).
Soften gelatin in cold water and add to hot custard.
Stir
to dissolve.
Remove 1 cup custard and add to chocolate chips.
Stir until melted.
Set aside.
To remaining cool custard, add rum and chill until mix begins to thicken.
Whip the cream and fold into chilled custard.
Tear cake into pieces and fold into custard.
Pour mix into 9-inch spring-form pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle chocolate custard over top and sprinkle with almonds.
Chill to set.
Garnish with sweet whipped cream and strawberries.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in 1/2 of the semi-sweet and white chocolates and 1/2 cup of the walnuts.
Spread in greased foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan. Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Sprinkle with remaining semi-sweet and white chocolates.
Cover with foil.
Let stand 5 minutes or until chocolates are melted.
Swirl chocolates with small knife to marbleize.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup walnuts.
Cool in pan until chocolate is firm.
Cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Measure and combine remaining dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and put aside.
Add buttermilk, bananas and vanilla to creamed mixture.
Mix well. Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 1 (10 x 4 x 2-inch) pan, 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf and 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Sprinkle with lime juice before serving.
Serve as relish with vegetables or as a dip for tortilla chips.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix and let stand overnight in refrigerator, uncovered!

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Combine salt, dry mustard and pepper. Sprinkle over meat and pound with mallet.
In heavy skillet, brown steak slowly on both sides in hot oil.
Drain fat.
Drain mushrooms, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
Add mushroom liquid and Worcestershire sauce to skillet.
Cover and cook 1 3/4 to 2 hours. Add mushrooms a few minutes.

title: quick - easy coffee cake
directions: Crust:
Press biscuit dough into a 9-inch pie pan.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Saute onion in melted margarine.
Add mushrooms, rice, consomme, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart dish. Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Wash and pick over cranberries.
Bring them to a boil with sugar and water.
When berries pop, remove from heat.
Coarsely chop unpeeled oranges or put them through a grinder. When berries have cooled, add the oranges and serve.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven.
Saute onion and celery until tender.
Add flour, stirring until smooth (1 minute).
Gradually add milk, broth and bouillon.
Cook over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly until slightly thickened.
Add seasoning. Stir in cheeses until melted.
Add broccoli.
Cover and simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally; do not let soup boil.
Serve with croutons.

title: mom's scalloped corn
directions: Mix.
Bake in greased glass dish 1 hour at 350°.

title: celebration potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done.
Drain and cool.
Refrigerate until called for.
Chop next 5 ingredients and combine with mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, mustard and salt; mix well.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes.
Add potatoes to mixture and stir gently until well mixed.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
These may be rolled out and baked without rising.
You may also freeze after cutting out biscuits.
Can also be left in refrigerator for one week; roll out a few each day, if desired.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except chocolate chips and wax) and shape into balls on wax paper.
Melt one large 12 ounce package of chocolate chips and 1/2 square of paraffin wax in a double broiler.
Dip balls in the chocolate and place on wax paper.
Leave to set until chocolate hardens.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut,
core
and quarter apples;
add water.
Bring to a boil; simmer
for
hour.
Drain water, but reserve.	Put apples through
colander; add water to attain desired consistency.
Add sugar
and cinnamon as desired.
Fill clean jars; seal with hot water bath for 20 minutes.	Remove and cool.

title: perfect quiche lorraine
directions: Line a 10-inch pie pan with pastry.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes; remove from oven.
Gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Cool on rack.

title: hot barbecue
directions: Heat together the first five ingredients.
Add chipped ham or use hot dogs, cut into small pieces.
Serve on buns.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add boiling water to jello;
stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and salt.
Put aside
to
partly set.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Put into a 4 x 8-inch loaf pan or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: authentic toll house cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Beat shortening, sugars, vanilla and water until creamy.
Add flour mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: stir 'n roll pastry
directions: Mix flour and salt together.
Measure oil, milk and water in same cup.
But don't stir together.
Pour all at once into flour. Stir until mixed.
Press into smooth ball.
Cut into halves. Flatten slightly.
Roll between sheets of waxed paper.
If dough tears, mend without moistening.

title: dip(for microwave)
directions: In a microwave-safe pan (glass) spread cream cheese on bottom. Pour salsa over cream cheese.
Put shredded cheese over salsa, then chopped olives (if desired).
Heat in microwave for about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mound candy
directions: Bring syrup to boil.
Add coconut.
Stir and let stand 1 hour. Shape into balls and dip into Candy-Quick or almond bark.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Use liquid from cherries and pineapple with water added to make the cup of water. Bring to a boil. Add gelatin and dissolve; add ice cream to hot gelatin and mix until melted. Fold in other ingredients; pour into mold or flat dish or bowl. Sets up within 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Stir together salad dressing and mustard.
Combine potatoes, salt, pepper, onion and pickles. Pour dressing over potato combination.
Mix lightly.
Carefully stir in eggs.
Chill and serve.

title: mexi-dogs
directions: Place hot dog on tortilla shell.
Add salsa and Cheddar cheese; roll hot dog and mixture together in tortilla shell. Place in microwave for 30 seconds or until fully heated.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl stir together all ingredients except eggs and oil.
Pour eggs and oil over flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Turn into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack for 15 minutes before removing from pan to cool further.

title: glazed carrots pecan
directions: Peel carrots and cut into large slices.
Sprinkle salt over carrots and saute in margarine until crisp.
Do not overcook. Spoon honey over carrots.
Add pecans and stir until they have a glaze.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season pork chops.
Beat egg and milk together.
Dip pork chops in egg mixture, then into corn flake crumbs.
Place in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Turn pork chops once halfway through cooking period.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with 1/2 cup soup, broth and eggs.
Spread into casserole dish.
Top with diced chicken.
Combine remaining soup with milk; pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until set in a 350° oven.

title: troll cookies(hulderkaker)
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until white.
Add eggs and syrup and blend well.
Sift in flour, spices and baking powder.
Roll into balls the size of walnut.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press a blanched almond into each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large serving bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: simply delicious granola
directions: Stir the oats, brown sugar, wheat germ, coconut and the almonds until blended. Heat the oil, honey and vanilla in a small pan until bubbling. Thoroughly mix liquids with the dry ingredients.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Spread rice in pan and cover with meat mixture. (browned hamburger, taco sauce, chili and green chilies).
Cover this with the soup and milk mixed together. Top with broken nacho chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: olan's boiled cookies
directions: In a saucepan, combine oleo, sugar, canned milk and cocoa. Place on fire and bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix; put into well greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: egg nog
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk, ice cream and whipping cream.
Beat whipping cream until it begins to thicken.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.

title: sugarless banana orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking powder and soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix bananas, orange juice and eggs until well blended.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Add dry ingredients and stir until just moistened.

title: pot pie
directions: Make gravy using first 5 ingredients plus juice from choplets. Let simmer.
Peel and dice potatoes and boil until tender.
Peel and slice carrots and boil until tender.
Dip choplets in flour and brown in oil; cut into cubes.
Add vegetables and meat to gravy in an 8 x 8-inch pan and cover with a crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: portguise bum soup
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and cook for 20 minutes.
Add salt and cabbage; add water to cover and cook 20 minutes more.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and potato chips. Place 1/2 teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool for awhile.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: caramel fudge brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup condensed milk.
Pour 2/3 batter into 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup condensed milk together.
Sprinkle chips over brownies.
Spread melted caramels over chips.
Spread the rest of the batter over the top.
Bake for an additional 20 minutes.

title: banana fish
directions: Mix together flour, curry powder and soy sauce; coat bananas and fish; set aside.
Heat oil in skillet.
Stir-fry celery until crisp; set aside.
Add butter to oil; saute bananas until golden, about 1 minute on each side.
Sprinkle bananas with half of lemon juice; remove to serving dish.
Saute fish in oil/butter mix until fish comes easily away on a fork, about 3 minutes on each side. Sprinkle with remaining lemon juice.
Place on serving dish with bananas.
Spoon celery over fish.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix above in order given using large mixing bowl.
Pour into 3 loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°.
You can make two loaf pans but it will be very high in center.
This freezes very well.

title: creamy vinaigrette salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight-fitting lid and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: beef stew in a crock-pot
directions: Cut stew meat in 1-inch pieces.
Mix with soup mix and pepper; place in the bottom of the crock-pot.
Add the barley evenly over meat mixture.
Layer celery, carrots, onions and potatoes.
Pour water over all (or tomato juice, if preferred).
Cover and set on high for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix evenly and completely at this time. Set on low to complete cooking.
Time is up to you, depending on your taste for crunchy or well done vegetables.

title: sauce with sausage and chickpeas
directions: Remove sausage casings.
Heat olive oil in a large saucepan and add sausage meat.
Cook until meat is no longer pink, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up lumps.
Drain off fat.
Add sauce, chickpeas and olives.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Toss with cooked pasta. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and serve!

title: cabbage pineapple salad
directions: Grate the cabbage into bowl. Drain the pineapple and add to cabbage.
Add the sugar and salt to taste.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten thoroughly. Blend together and serve.
You may substitute raisins and chopped apples for the pineapple.

title: pico de gallo sauce(salsa)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as a dip or over fresh grilled meat, especially fish and chicken.
Serves 8.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add beef broth, chicken broth, tomato juice, cumin, chili powder, jalapeno, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Add chicken and tomato.
Place tortilla chips in bowls and fill with hot soup.
Garnish with avocado strips and cheese. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: I use 3 tablespoons of pumpkin pie spice to replace spices listed.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix filling ingredients in order given and pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes or until knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: cold spaghetti dish
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Mix the rest of ingredients and toss well to mix flavors.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate Kisses and last 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape dough into balls using a rounded teaspoonful for each. Roll balls in last 1/2 cup sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 8 minutes. Take out and put candy Kiss on each. Press down firmly so cookie cracks around edge. Bake another 3 to 5 minutes in preheated moderate oven at 350°.

title: light potato salad
directions: In a large bowl whisk together mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill before serving.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Cook 2 pounds of chicken breasts in 2 to 3 cups of water until tender.
Remove skin and bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Heat broth, milk and celery soup.
Slowly add flour, salt and pepper.

title: sweet potato cranberry casserole
directions: Add potato, cranberry sauce and bread in a casserole dish. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot top with oleo.

title: best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips. Form into balls and bake in preheated oven, 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 3 dozen, approximately.

title: brussels sprouts supreme
directions: Place Brussels sprouts in bottom of square dish (9 or 10-inch).
Pour in beef bouillon, mixing in salt and Cajun seasoning.
Pour can of tomatoes along with juice over Brussels sprouts.
Cook until tender and most juice has evaporated.
Place grated cheese over cooked dish and return to oven for 10 minutes. You may add mushrooms to mixture when starting if desired.
Makes great main dish.
Put in oven at 350°.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend shortening, then thoroughly mix grated cheese into mixture.
Stir in milk.
Roll onto floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: evergreen punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar and 1 cup cold water.
Add juice from the 3 lemons (strained) and the fruit juices.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
May add a few drops of green food coloring.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water and blend in soup. Mix in meat, onion and pepper.
Turn meat mixture into pastry lined pie plate.
Cover with top crust. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes, then reduce oven to 350° and continue to bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered crackers and peanut butter
directions: Make peanut butter and crackers.
Put white almond bark over low heat and melt.
Then add chocolate chips and melt.
Dip cookies into chocolate.
Put on wax paper and cool.

title: sausage and cabbage dinner
directions: Cut sausage in thin slices (1-inch or less) and brown in a large pot.
Add water, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic and onion. Core and quarter cabbage.
Add it to pot.
Cover and cook on medium-high until cabbage is well cooked (30 to 40 minutes).
Stir occasionally.
Slice cornbread in large pieces.
Lay open faced on plate and spoon sausage and cabbage on top.

title: eileen's easy dip
directions: In a saucepan, heat the chili and stir in the cream cheese until melted with the chili.
Put in a serving bowl and dip away with the chips.
(Optional:
Melt Cheddar cheese on the top!)

title: ham sandwiches
directions: Put in blender.
Blend one minute.
May either spread sandwiches and freeze or freeze mixture in container for later use.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Cover and cook.
Mash this mixture when tender.
Thicken mixture with 2 tablespoons flour mixed in small amount of water, stirring fast, and simmer.
Add 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese.
Simmer until melted.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 1/4 cups of milk.

title: taco quiche
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and milk.
Add biscuit mix and pepper; mix well.
Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread sour cream over the top.
Sprinkle with lettuce, tomato, green pepper, onions and cheese.

title: braided orange bread
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour and undissolved yeast in large mixing bowl.
Scald milk in saucepan.
Add margarine, sugar and salt. Cool to very warm (120° to 130°).
Add milk mixture to flour-yeast mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour, orange juice and rind.
Beat until mixed well.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: peach jello
directions: Combine jello, sugar and pineapple in pot and bring to a boil; let cool.
Add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Let congeal and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: In large bowl, combine sour cream and mayonnaise.
Stir in soup mix, mixing well.
Fold in drained spinach and other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 to 2 hours.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: You will need a large oven bag (14 x 20-inch).

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix the sugar, flour, salt and milk together.
Pour over butter in casserole dish. Pour the pie filling over.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Combine crushed crackers, flour, salt, pepper and Mrs.
Dash (seasonings to taste).
Dip chicken fillets in egg and coat with cracker mixture.
Fry chicken in large skillet (approximately 1/3 full of oil) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel-covered plate and top with cheese while still hot.
While chicken is frying, prepare noodles as directed and warm spaghetti sauce. Serve chicken on a bed of noodles topped with spaghetti sauce.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa. Add syrup and milk; bring to a boil. Cook on medium heat for 2 minutes. Stir often. Add peanut butter, margarine and oats. Stir until mixed. Spoon on waxed paper. Yields 60 cookies.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix in order given, adding shoestrings just before serving. Refrigerate.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough in 1/8-inch slices and cover pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and almond extract; spread over crust.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream together cocoa, sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour.
Measure and sift again with soda.
Add alternately with milk, beating until batter is smooth. Bake in 3 layers at 350°.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone and set broth aside.
Mix chicken with onion, pimentos, season to taste and set aside.
In a heavy skillet heat about 2 tablespoons of oil.
Very quickly drop corn tortillas into skillet, turning once but do not brown or fry. As you take each tortilla out, pat dry with paper towels.
Fill each tortilla with chicken mixture.
Roll and place tortillas in a 9-inch by 12-inch baking dish.
Cover with sour cream; pour 2 1/2 to 3 cups of chicken broth over them (to fill half of the baking dish).
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Heat oil
in pan.
Add onions and simmer.
Add the rest of the ingredients, mix well.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Cook egg, juice, cornstarch and sugar until thickened.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Mix and chill.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Put all ingredients in 2-quart pan. Cook on low on top of stove for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: english muffins
directions: Add butter, salt and sugar to milk; cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in water.
Add yeast, egg and 2 cups of flour to cooled milk.
Stir to blend well, then knead in remaining flour until firm and elastic.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cut shortening into flour, salt, baking powder and soda with pastry cutter or use your fingers until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Stir in buttermilk.
Turn out on floured board, kneading gently.
Roll out and cut large biscuits. Bake on a cookie sheet with biscuits touching each other for about 12 minutes.
Save you biscuit trimmings and roll rectangle. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll lengthwise and cut into 1/2-inch pieces for bite size kid pleasers.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Mix well. Fold in Cool Whip and freeze. Take out of freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Stir in Blue cheese. Cover, chill 2 hours.
Yields 2 cups.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together; chill.
Serve with fruit.

title: frozen fruit salad(serves 12)
directions: Mash bananas (I use mixer), then add fruits and Special Dressing.
Fold in whipped cream.
May be frozen in refrigerator trays or in large pan in freezer.
If dressing is desired as topping, double the dressing recipe.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes by hand.
Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork pot pie
directions: Mix and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Blend together and shape dough into balls.
Place in tassie pans and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and push Reese's cup in center.
Let stand 10 minutes in pan, then remove.

title: aunt flossie's lemon bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add grated lemon rind, flour, salt, baking powder, eggs and milk.
Mix and bake at 350° for 55 minutes in greased and floured pan.

title: easy pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Put in prepared pie shell.
Chill overnight.
Slice and top with cherries to serve.

title: orange-pineapple ice cream
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and finish filling freezer with milk.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Combine everything except the cheese and worcestershire sauce and
place into pastry crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Toss cheese with worcestershire sauce, sprinkle over the top of pie.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: roasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Combine all ingredients in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir often.

title: fried pies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening until it is like meal.
Add milk. Turn onto a floured board, roll 1/8-inch thick. Cut in 3-inch squares.
Put 1 teaspoon of thickened fruit filling in center.
Fold in triangles and pinch edges well.
Fry in deep fat.
Drain and dust generously with powdered sugar.

title: artichoke bread
directions: Mix all together well; turn into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Cut and serve either warm or cold.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Dredge	chops in mixture of flour, mustard, garlic salt and pepper.
Brown in small amount of oil.
Place in crock-pot with a layer
of
onion and parsley between chops.
Add soup. Do not stir.
Cover
and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Even more delicious if	you substitute 3 or 4 tablespoons fresh parsley for the parsley flakes.
The rest of the supper menu could be served
with steamed rice, buttered English peas, fruit salad and hot French bread.

title: roetken's fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together vegetable oil, vanilla, eggs, and sugar.
Sift together salt, flour, soda, and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture. Fold in apples and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Pour
all
ingredients except bread into greased casserole dish.
Top	with bread crumb mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: black bean and corn salsa
directions: Cook corn until crisp and tender; drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.

title: home style vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle, combine stew meat, water, bouillon cubes and bay leaves. Bring water to boil; simmer covered for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender. Cool stock; Skim fat from surface. Add tomatoes, carrots, celery, onion, cabbage, potatoes, pepper and garlic powder; simmer covered for 40 minutes. Add corn; cook an additional 10 minutes. Serve with french bread and crackers.

title: sugar nuts
directions: Cook sugar, cinnamon and milk until it forms a soft ball.
Add vanilla and walnuts. Cook until thick and grainy, stirring constantly!
Turn out mixture on waxed paper.
Separate nuts quickly with a fork.
Let cool real good.

title: marinate delight
directions: Drain all the vegetables and mix together.
Boil together remaining ingredients and cool.
Pour over vegetables. Refrigerate overnight.

title: praline brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine the dark brown sugar, 1/4 cup butter and milk; stir over low heat just until butter is melted.
Pour into an ungreased 8-inch square baking pan; sprinkle evenly with pecans.

title: grandma eller's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut oven back to 350° when pie is inserted.
Bake until brown.

title: casserole mexicana
directions: Heat oil in skillet over moderately high heat.
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned.
Add seasoning mix, undrained beans, corn and tomato sauce.
Stir to combine.
Bring to a boil. Pour mixture into a deep 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle olives over meat mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled tortilla chips around the edge of casserole and sprinkle the cheese over the chips.
Place in a 350° oven and heat for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into 8 patties 2 inches in diameter.
Better if chilled a few hours.
Fry in deep fat (low cholesterol shortening) until golden brown.

title: tuna or chicken casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain well.
Soften cream cheese and blend into soup.
Stir in chicken or tuna, onion, mustard, milk and macaroni.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: salmon sandwiches
directions: Drain salmon and flake.
Combine all other ingredients.
Mix together.
Spread salmon mix on 6 buttered buns and wrap in foil. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25
minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, garlic salt, Worcestershire sauce and chopped nuts together.
Spread mixture on ham slices and roll up longways.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove and slice in 1-inch slices.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal mix, salt and onion.
Stir in milk and eggs. Let stand 3 minutes.
Drop batter, a teaspoon at a time, into deep, hot fat (360°).
Fry until golden on underside; turn and fry on other side.
Total cooking time is about 4 minutes.
Drain. Serve hot with fish.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen hush puppies.

title: curry chicken salad
directions: In large bowl, mix
together
chicken, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and almonds.
(Can be prepared up to 8 hours in advance.)

title: mommy's olive oil rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Add all dry ingredients to large mixing bowl.
Add olive oil and yeast mixture.
Beat with dough hooks for 5 to 7 minutes.
Let rise in bowl sprayed with cooking spray until double (cover with damp towel).
Shape into round rolls.
Brush tops with mixture of 1 egg white and 1/4 cup water.
Let rise.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts.
Roll into little balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 300°.
Take them out of oven when they begin to brown.
Remove from oven, roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Let cool.
Roll through powdered sugar again.

title: rose punch
directions: Heat water and sugar to boiling; cool.
Mix wine, juice and sugar into pitcher.
Stir in mineral water.
Place grapes into stemmed glasses.
Pour punch.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine all except mashed potatoes. Pour in 9 x 13 pan. Spoon mashed potatoes on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix crumbs and melted butter.
Pat in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, vanilla, stick of butter, egg and cream cheese together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread mixture over crumbs.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Mix Ricotta or cottage cheese, Mozzarella or American cheese, bread crumbs, salt, parsley and egg.
Boil lasagna noodles as directed.
Cut lasagna strips in half.
Spoon portion of cheese mixture on lasagna strips and roll up.

title: excellent oven stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a heavy 5 to 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cover and bake about 3 hours, stirring twice until meat is tender and sauce thickened.
Discard bay leaves before serving or refrigerating.
You can pretty much ignore this stew for the 3 hours, but remember that it will taste best if you make it a day or two ahead.
Refrigerate and reheat on stovetop.
You can throw in a 12 ounce can of mushrooms and 10 ounce package of frozen peas and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: orange refresher
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a blender and process at a high speed.
Add ice cubes, a few at a time, blending until slushy.
Serve immediately.

title: green noodle casserole
directions: Boil the chicken, bone and save broth.
Saute the onion, celery and bell pepper in the butter for 5 minutes.
Cut up the Velveeta cheese and stir into above mixture until melted.
Add the olives. Add the mushroom soup to the chicken, then add to sauteed ingredients.
Boil the noodles in the chicken broth.
Drain and mix all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Can make 1 day ahead of time and keep refrigerated.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Mash chicken breast with a wooden mallet.
Lay out, dull side up.
Place cheese on top.
Roll tightly and secure with toothpicks. Dip into eggs and milk.
Dip into bread crumbs.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Place 1/2 batter in ungreased Bundt pan.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Add remaining batter and repeat chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: veggie dip
directions: Blend onion, bouillon cubes and Tabasco until fine.
Add mayonnaise and cream cheese.
Enjoy!

title: chicken or turkey chow bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 1/2 cups noodles.
Put into greased casserole dish.
Put balance of noodles on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, water and mashed bananas, then add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add pecans last (I like dusting them very lightly with flour).
Bake in preheated 350° oven.
Makes 2 large loaves, 9 x 5-inch size loaf pans.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix sugar, Crisco or margarine, 1 cup warm water and yeast.
Add eggs, then flour and salt.
Mix well.
Dough will be soft; let rise until double (about 3 hours), covered.
Mix down with spoon or knife.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Two hours before serving, roll into desired shapes; cover and bake about 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: strawberries and vanilla microwave pudding
directions: Blend sugar and cornstarch in 1-quart casserole.
Gradually stir in milk and mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes. Stir every 3 minutes until mixture is smooth, thick and clear. Quickly stir small amount of hot pudding into beaten egg.
Return egg mixture into hot pudding.
Microwave on Medium-high for 1 to 3 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla; stir until margarine is melted.
Pour pudding over the strawberries and serve.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Mix together tuna, soup and milk in a 10-inch frying pan. Heat to boiling on medium.
Add 1 1/2 cups rice and cover for five minutes.
Uncover and let stand until thickened.

title: milk gravy
directions: Heat oil.
Add flour, salt, pepper and seasoning salt to taste.
Brown and add milk, stirring consistently.
Add more milk to make thin.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: microwave applesauce
directions: Cover in microwave-safe bowl: apples, water and sugar.
Cook on High for 12 to 14 minutes or until apples are tender.
Stir 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Put 1/2 vanilla wafer crumbs on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar with butter and chocolate.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour it over crumbs.
Spread ice cream over chocolate mixture.
Top with remaining vanilla wafer crumbs.
Cover and put in freezer overnight before serving.

title: cheese cake
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Beat Ricotta and cream cheese together.
Blend
in
eggs, one at a time.	Mix in vanilla and lemon juice;
pour in greased pan.	Bake 1 hour; cut oven off. Let cake
stay
in
oven
for	30 minutes longer.
Remove and cover. Refrigerate.

title: apple dessert
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Add the apples and nuts (thick batter); mix.
Bake 50 minutes at 325° in 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Serve with whipped topping.

title: spotted pup pudding
directions: Combine sugar, spices and salt; stir into rice.
Add milk, eggs and raisins.
Pour into a greased baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes, stirring once.

title: easy tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and serve.
Sweet pickle relish and salad dressing make a sweeter tartar sauce.
Mayonnaise and dill relish makes a more vinegary sauce.

title: chicken breasts with olivada
directions: * Olivada:
Black olives and oil.
Can be purchased in specialty section of grocery store.

title: dill vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients well by hand or in a food processor.
Chill overnight.

title: holland cream cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until smooth.
Add egg yolks, beating constantly.
Add flour and soda to mixture.
Add vanilla and buttermilk. Mix coconut and nuts and fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes in 9-inch pans.
Makes 3 layers.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini, onions, and salt into a large bowl.
Mix well. Let stand over-night.
Drain well an put into a kettle with remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: better next day slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion, carrots and apple in food processor. Mix all together.
Place in bowl with good lid covering.
Mix together salt, pepper, sugar, oil and vinegar.
Boil mixture and pour over cabbage mixture.
DO NOT STIR for 4 hours or over night. Then stir.
This will keep in refrigerator for days.

title: custard
directions: Bring to a boil.
Save egg whites.
Beat stiff and fold in after custard is done.

title: wassail
directions: In a large pan, heat the cider and cinnamon stick.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Keep over low heat or reheat in small batches as guests arrive.
Makes 20 cups.

title: marie's pumpkin dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill and serve with fruit.

title: fly off the handle pancakes!
directions: Sift together flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
In a separate bowl, mix egg, milk and sour cream.
Pour into dry ingredients and mix together with a fork or slotted spoon.
Add melted butter.
Let sit while you grease the griddle and warm it. Pour batter in small, round cakes.
When cakes are brown on one side and bubbly on top, flip over and cook a minute or so more.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and blend with milk. Add remaining ingredients except walnuts. Pat into 8 inch pie plate. Spread walnuts over top. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve hot with crackers or potato chips.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Butter bread; cut into cubes.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Sprinkle bread with sausage, then cheese. Beat eggs, salt, cream and mustard together.
Pour over bread mix. Chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: hot sausage biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, sausage and cheese.
Roll rounded teaspoonful of dough into a ball.
Makes about 100 biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread thaw at least 3 to 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°. Grease cookie sheet.
Roll out dough lengthwise approximately 2 feet.
Add pizza sauce.
Layer with cheese.
Layer with pepperoni.
Layer with capicola ham.
Continue until all used up. Take the ends, bring together and pinch ends together and form a ring.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oven baked chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in bag.
Roll 1 cut up chicken in melted margarine.
Shake pieces in bag.
Bake 45 minutes; turn and bake 15 minutes more.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box. Fry onions, bell pepper and hamburger meat together. Drain. Mix macaroni, onions, pepper, hamburger meat with mushroom soup, whole kernel corn, salt and pepper. Put in baking dish in 400° oven or until onions are tender.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except marshmallows, in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed in mixer.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Use 1/4 cup mix and 3/4 cup boiling water.

title: rindsrouladen
directions: Lay the slices of beef flat; season them with salt and pepper. Spread 1 teaspoon of mustard over each slice.
Put 1 piece of bacon on the end of each slice, along with 1 tablespoon chopped onion and sliced pickle.
Roll the beef up tight, making sure that it is well closed.
Heat bacon drippings in a heavy pan or kettle; add the beef rolls.
Saute on all sides until nicely browned.
Add the onions; saute for another minute.
Add the diluted consomme and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 2 hours.
Remove meat and place on a preheated serving platter.
Mix flour and butter with water; add to the gravy.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour some of the gravy over the Rouladen and sprinkle some parsley over it.

title: shrimp creole for two
directions: Saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomato sauce, oregano and bay leaf.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in shrimp and simmer 5 minutes.
(If using fresh shrimp, simmer until shrimp tests done; do not overcook shrimp. If mixture appears too thin, thicken with a small amount of cornstarch dissolved in small amount of water.)
Remove bay leaf before serving over hot cooked rice.
Yield:
2 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread 2 packages or crescent rolls onto a cookie sheet. Press together and bake according to package directions.
Cool. If using pizza crust, bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
May be made the night before.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and add enough water to make 2 3/4 cups liquid.
Boil.
Pour over jello.
Put in refrigerator until sticky.
Add blueberries and pineapple (do not drain pineapple). Put back in refrigerator.
Keep until firm (about 2 hours).
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Pour over jello and top with nuts.

title: good brownies
directions: Boil water, oleo and cocoa in pan, just until melted.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and soda; pour cocoa over this.
Add 2 eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well and pour into large cookie sheet. Bake 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: susie's appetizer
directions: Brown meats together; drain, then pat with paper towels. In large bowl, mix in cheese until melted, then add remaining ingredients. Put on rye bread. Place on cookie sheet and freeze.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and season.
Drain well.
Arrange meat, potatoes (sliced thin), soup and cheese (on top).
Cover.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Mix together and set aside sour cream, sugar and 2 1/2 packages coconut.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and bake in three 8 to 9-inch layer pans (grease and line pans with wax paper).
Bake until cake top springs back when touched. Remove from pan and turn layers upside-down.
Spread with coconut-sour cream mixture.
Wrap in plastic wrap and place in refrigerator.
Best if refrigerated for 3 to 4 days.
Cover top and sides of cake with Cool Whip before serving.

title: mom's spinach cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place butter or margarine in an 8-inch square baking dish and set in oven just long enough for butter to melt, about 2 minutes.
Tilt dish to coat bottom and sides with melted butter; set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: drop sand tarts
directions: Beat egg whites and add last to butter, sugar and flour.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Grease pan one time.
Flour pan each time before baking cookies.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 90 to 100 cookies.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: meat marinade
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
