Use any kind of meat you prefer and marinate for 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
You can reserve marinade after meat is marinated. Refrigerate and use several times.

title: german heavenly earth cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on box.
Set aside. Layer in bottom of greased pan: coconut and pecans.
Pour cake mix over coconut and pecans.
Cream together cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake mixture, a spoonful at a time, evenly.
Bake at 350° until tested done, about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix 1/2 of cream cheese
and 1/2 cup of the mayonnaise, green onions and ham.
Add
nuts;
mix well.
Shape into ball. Combine other 1/4 cup of
mayonnaise
and
other
1/2 of cream cheese. Mix well.
Spread
this mixture over ham ball.
Chill well.
Cover ham ball with chopped nuts.

title: old fashioned baked coon
directions: Parboil raccoon pieces until tender.
Place in baking dish and sprinkle with sage, salt and pepper.
Add broth.
Precook sweet potatoes, cut in half and place around the raccoon.
Bake in 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift
together	flour, sugar, baking soda, salt, spices and cocoa.
Add the next six ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased
9	x 13-inch (or smaller) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Add cheese to sauteed vegetables and let melt before adding soups.
Mix in rice and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: Cube or slice in strips the meat.
Brown in oil.
Add garlic and onion.
Continue browning.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until meat is tender.
Add water as needed during cooking.

title: yummy zucchini
directions: Put sliced zucchini and onion in large skillet with melted margarine.
Saute until zucchini is transparent.
While it is cooking, break bread in bowl and cover with milk.
Add bread to zucchini and season.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, until blended. Serve as side dish with any meat entree.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add egg mixture and blend.
Spray pie pan with Pam or grease well. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until puffy and browned.
It makes its own crust.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
In a smaller bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture, a little at a time, until all is used.
Add pecans and raisins.

title: *grape-nuts bread
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together, then add flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
(You may add 1 cup raisins or dates.)

title: chuck wagon stew(club member: jason harvey)
directions: Brown meat with onions and green pepper. Remove excess grease. Add corn and Ranch beans (including liquid). Add tomatoes with green chilies, tomato soup and seasoning.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg together.
Press evenly into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (not floured).
Mix box of powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs (use mixer).
Put on top of cake mixture in pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
(When it cools, center will fall in.)

title: pineapple punch
directions: Pour juices into punch bowl.
Add scoops of sherbet and pour 7-Up in last.

title: raisin muffins
directions: Boil raisins and water together until only 1 cup liquid is left.
Cool and add baking soda.
Cream shortening, sugar and egg. Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisin mixture.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into greased or paper-lined cupcake tins and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: frijole mole chili
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large pan until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except optional toppings.
Boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Uncover; continue to simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Ladle into bowls with additional picante sauce.
Serves 6.

title: orange amaretto yams
directions: Cook yams in boiling, salted water just until tender; drain and peel them.
Cut into thick slices and arrange in a glass baking dish.
Cream together margarine, sugar, orange juice, rind and Amaretto.
Cover yams with sauce and bake in a 375° oven until surface is nicely browned.
Cook 10 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: beef-rice casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown meat with chopped onion.
Drain well. Add remaining ingredients and cook on top of stove until rice and celery are cooked.
Pour off any excess liquid.
Add sour cream and serve.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in a blender until smooth. Serve as a dip for apple slices.

title: fiesta confetti
directions: Note:
Need 3 to 4 taco salad bowls.

title: finger salad
directions: Put crescent rolls on cookie sheet to resemble a crust, pinching together the perforations and bake according to package instructions.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing and spread over cooled crust.
Shred vegetables and cheese.
Mix together.
Sprinkle on top, then press firmly so it will stay together.
Cut and serve.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients
until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Put in cold water.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until dull and ready for pan.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine juice, egg, flour, sugar and vinegar. Cook until thick.
Cool.
In a large bowl combine pineapple, apples, marshmallows, 1/2 cup peanuts and the cooled mixture. Fold in Cool Whip.
Sprinkle remainder of peanuts on top. Refrigrate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Great for picnics, barbecues and potlucks.
Kids will love it!
Pineapple juice prevents apples from turning brown so this salad can be made the night before.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel and boil carrots until tender.
Brush with butter. Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Stir well.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring often.

title: no egg cookies
directions: Mix together butter, sugar and water until creamy.
Add the rest of the ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Place batter on plastic wrap and roll into 1-inch logs.
Chill for 35 minutes. Cut dough and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for about 11 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll in small balls.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake on 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges are brown.
Do not let brown all over.

title: dot's bleu cheese flan
directions: Combine crackers and butter.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Adjust oven rack to be 1/3 down from top of oven and preheat to 400°.
Butter an 11 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside. Blanch and peel peaches.
Cut in half and remove pits, then cut halves into wide slices.
You should have 6 cups of sliced peaches.
Place in wide bowl.
Combine lemon juice and vanilla and drizzle over peaches; toss gently.
Place peaches in baking dish.

title: marinated vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables. Pour dressing over vegetables. Cover. Marinate overnight. Drain vegetables. Arrange on lettuce leaves.

title: no fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat.
Fold in the Marshmallow Creme.
Spread on top of any cream pie and bake in a 300° oven for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Pour all ingredients into a casserole dish.
Add butter on top.
Do not mix.
Do not add water to soup.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour 9 x 13 inch pan. Prepare the cake mix as directed on the box.
Mix the nuts and coconut together and spread over the bottom the pan.
Pour prepared cake batter over pecan/coconut mixture.
Melt oleo and cream cheese together in a saucepan; add sugar.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix and let set overnight in fridge before serving.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine hamburger, onion, eggs and rice in a bowl. Make into meat balls and put in roaster pan (covered). Mix tomato soup with 1/2 can water. Pour over meat balls and bake in a 350° oven for about 2 hours or until meat balls are done. Add water if needed. Great with mashed potatoes or rice.

title: chicken orange casserole
directions: Mix ginger, salt and pepper.
Rub into chicken.
Melt butter and/or oil; brown chicken.
Drain chicken. Place in single layer in casserole.
Saute onion and shredded peel of 1/2 orange.
Blend flour with a little orange juice.
Add remainder of orange juice and cider, then add to onion.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Blend in syrup.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and arrange orange segments or slices over chicken.
Continue to cook 15 to 20 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: vegetable-rice soup with saffron
directions: Bring 1 cup of the broth and the saffron to a boil in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat, cover and let steep for 15 minutes. Bring remaining 7 cups of broth to a boil in a 5-quart pot.
Stir in saffron broth, escarole, green beans, carrots and rice.
Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring often, until vegetables are tender.
Add yellow squash and tomatoes.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes longer, until rice is tender.
Season with pepper.

title: pot roast and vegetables
directions: Put vegetables in slow cooker. Salt and pepper the roast.
Put on top of vegetables. Add water; cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 5 hours.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients for 10 minutes on medium heat until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cool water.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Beat until mixture thickens well.
(Just soft enough to get out of the cooker.)
Pour into pan or dish.
Let set until hardened and cut into squares.
Store in airtight containers.

title: susie's best ever cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: rich chocolate beet bread
directions: Puree beets with juice and transfer to large bowl.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients and add to beet mixture and mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in three 8 x 4 x 2 bread pans about 3/4 full.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rave coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "stretcher" oyster stew
directions: Cook potatoes in water with salt added until almost soft, about 10 minutes.
Add oysters and liquid. Bring just to a boil. Remove from heat at once. Add butter, cream and seasonings.
Cover and let stand about 15 minutes before serving. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat together milk and cream cheese. Pour over fruit and mix well. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate peanut squares
directions: Melt butter and 2 (1 ounce) chocolate squares together.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, coconut and peanuts.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: liver and bacon roll-ups
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Roll liver in flour mix.
Roll bacon around liver, then roll liver and bacon in flour mix.
Put toothpick in center of bacon and liver to hold together and fry until done.

title: chicken curry
directions: Cook onion and apple in oleo until clear.
Blend in flour, curry powder, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir in chicken broth and lemon juice; add raisins.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add chicken.
Heat and serve over rice.

title: party mix
directions: Combine oil, Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt and salt, mixing well.
Pour over nuts, cereal and pretzels.
Stir very well. Bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: no bake pie desert
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Put in pie shell and refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with Cool Whip.
Can also slice bananas in bottom of pie shell before adding ingredients.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in the water until tender.
Drain off liquid and save.
Mash potatoes.
Measure liquid and add enough milk to make 3 cups.
Slowly stir liquid into potatoes.
Add margarine, salt and pepper as desired.
Simmer a few minutes, then serve.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; cook until tender.
Drain broth; set aside.
Discard vegetables; debone chicken; set aside.
Use 1 1/2 cups of broth; bring to boil.
Add 1 cup uncooked rice; cook until tender.
Combine chicken, rice and cream of chicken soup in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for no longer than 10 minutes.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add vinegar, vanilla, oil and water.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: california mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes or until potatoes are very tender; drain.
Return potatoes to saucepan; mash.
Stir in parsley, onion soup blended with hot milk and sour cream.

title: chilies and cheese pie(appetizer)
directions: Drain.
Place chilies in shallow 9-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour 1/2 over chilies; sprinkle cheese over top and add remaining eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until of custard consistency.
Serve hot on crackers.

title: pumpkin cake in a jar
directions: You will also need 8 pint size wide mouth jars with lids and rings for sealing and 8 wax paper circles, cut to fit inside canning jars.

title: quick cheese bread
directions: Using 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine, grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
Use 2 (8 ounce) packages of refrigerated biscuits to fill each of the pans.
Arrange 1 package (10 biscuits) standing up on their ends along each long side.
Sprinkle each with 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until breads are a deep golden brown.
Remove and cool on wire racks. Sprinkle each with a little chopped chives or parsley.

title: spicy grilled catfish
directions: Arrange fillets in a shallow dish.
In a jar, combine lemon juice, soy sauce, vegetable oil, ginger, garlic, green onions, minced onions, paprika and cayenne pepper.
Pour over catfish and cover.
Marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours. Remove fish from marinade.
Grill or broil 4 minutes on each side or until catfish flakes with fork.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter in buttermilk over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Stir all well.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: easy homemade rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine on low heat only until the margarine is melted.
Cool a few minutes.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add 1/4 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured board 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide into 12 pieces (you may shape into balls if you like, I simply place in 8-inch greased round pan).
Let rise until double.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: tingalings(no bake)
directions: Melt chips. Mix in noodles and nuts. Drop onto wax paper. Make small with different shapes. Wait until they harden.

title: soda cracker cake
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until stiff and dry.
Slowly add sugar, beating well.
Fold in cracker crumbs and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and top with favorite pie filling and then put a layer of Cool Whip.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Season the chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine the honey and soy sauce.
Pour over the chicken and bake for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and onion as package directs.
Drain well and combine broccoli with stuffing mix.
Put in greased casserole and pour melted butter over top.

title: garden style pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray 14-inch round pizza pan or 15 x 10-inch
jelly roll pan with vegetable oil cooking spray or oil lightly.
Combine
flour,
oat
flour,
baking powder and salt. Add
milk and oil; stir with fork until mixture forms a ball. Knead
dough on lightly floured surface about 10 times. With greased
fingers,
press
dough into prepared pan; shape edge to form rim.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: meat loaf for two
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine the first 5 ingredients.
In shallow baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 40 minutes until done. Top with tomato sauce during last 5 minutes of baking.

title: german chocolate turtle bars
directions: Place caramels in a double boiler and add 1/3 cup milk.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat; add cake mix, margarine, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts, stir.
Press 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle chips over this crust.
Pour the rest of the mix into pan and bake for additional 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: recipe of age
directions: Take all the years of your life and pour them into a huge kettle of memories from the past.
Add a large helping of love, a few old tears, a large portion of laughter, then spice with a sigh or two from other years.
Place kettle on the slow fire of hope and stir slowly with the ladle of humility.
Add a heaping cupful of faith.
Stir mixture with the spoon of experience and thicken with a few old dreams to give mixture just the right degree of nostalgia and simmer over slow fire of time.
Add smidgen of regret and a sip of sadness to keep mixture from becoming overly sweet.
Spice mixture with a few dreams for tomorrow.
Let cook and before serving sprinkle with the dust from a few old rainbows.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, nutmeg, soda and cinnamon.
Add to shortening, eggs and sugars mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and chopped nuts.
Bake in 350° oven.
Allow to cool before spreading on topping.

title: daiquiri slush
directions: Mix ingredients in a large plastic container and freeze.
Stir occasionally.
Daiquiri is always "mushy frozen" and ready to serve topped with a cherry.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch orange juice nutmeg and cook over low heat until thick.
Pour over carrots, let set and serve hot.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and peppers and pour into greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle chili peppers on top of batter. Add grated cheese and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs; add melted chocolate over hot water and beat thoroughly.
Mix flour, salt and nut meats; add vanilla extract and mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes. Cool; cut into squares.

title: cherry chip brownies
directions: Combine pie filling, cake mix, eggs and almond extract in a large bowl; mix until well blended.
Spread in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Cool.

title: cottage cheese tarts
directions: Cream fat. Add salt and vanilla. Blend well. Add flour. Chill dough about 3 hours. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut into 3-inch squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the package.
Drain and add the ingredients in order given except for cracker crumbs or onion rings.
Pour in greased casserole dish; top with crumbs or onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: no fail pound cake
directions: Cream powdered sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat after each egg.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add flour. Beat well.
Put in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Soak raw chicken in buttermilk for several hours.
Drain, leaving chicken wet with buttermilk.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Dredge chicken in crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle oil over the chicken and bake another 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese and cinnamon
directions: For each serving, spread toast with low-fat cottage cheese and sprinkle with sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Put under broiler or in toaster-oven until sugar-cinnamon mixture bubbles.
Serve at once. Yield:
1 serving.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Stir cornmeal into 2 cups milk. Heat mixture to a boil, stirring constantly, until it makes a mush. Add rest of milk and beaten eggs. Stir in salt, baking powder and melted butter. Pour into a greased 2 qt. casserole and bake for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry angel cake
directions: Prepare jello, using 1 cup water.
When slightly thickened, stir in raspberries and yogurt.
Pour over angel food cake which has been torn into 3/4-inch pieces.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage. Add soup mix; stir. Add cheese and melt. Put 1 tablespoon of meat mixture on a crescent roll triangle. Fold short corners over and then roll to close. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: christmas holly
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt margarine and marshmallows.
Stir in food coloring and vanilla.
Bring to boil and remove from heat. Quickly stir in frosted corn flakes and coat well.
Drop by tablespoons on waxed paper.
Place about 3 cinnamon candies or small cut candied cherries on each cluster to resemble berries. Let cool and dry out.

title: hot rolls
directions: Knead ingredients.
Spray pan with Pam cooking spray.
Let rise in pan.
Grease hands; pinch out in small balls.
Put 2 small balls in cookie pan; let rise again.
Bake until done at approximately 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with first 4 ingredients.
When well mixed, form into balls.
Melt 1/2 block wax.
Add chocolate chips. When melted, dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper.

title: chocolate chews
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cocoa, & milk in saucepan on high heat. Stir until boiling then quickly turn heat to medium.
Stir and boil for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts and vanilla to mixture and blend well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper. refrigerate to chill.
Serve.

title: black walnut icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix together.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Last add black walnuts.
Form into rolls (length you desire).
Place on wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Cover with wax paper and place in freezer or refrigerator until hard.
Slice and bake on a greased cookie sheet at 375° for approximately 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Spread peanut butter between two Ritz crackers until you have 48 cookie sandwiches and dip them in Chocolate Mix.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until thick; add Eagle Brand milk, then Cool Whip.
Put vanilla wafers and bananas in a long dish. Pour first mixture over.

title: thirty minute chocolate cake
directions: In bowl, cream sugar and margarine.
Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Pour over first mixture and stir.
Add flour, soda, salt, egg, buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir all together well.
Bake in greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Saute in butter the almonds and bread cubes.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: luncheon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in the 2 tablespoons lukewarm water. Scald milk, sugar, salt and shortening in top of double boiler. Pour mixture into large bowl.
Add cold water.
Cool to lukewarm. Add egg, dissolved yeast and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat for 3 minutes and stir in remaining flour.
Turn on lightly floured board and knead until smooth.
Shape into rolls and set in warm place for 1 1/2 hours or store dough covered in refrigerator until needed. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: louise's sloppy joe's
directions: Combine all ingredients. Cook in crock-pot on low for 8 hours or at 325° for 4 hours.
Stir to break up meat.

title: whiskey slushes
directions: In a large plastic container with lid combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Add water.
Mix well.
Place in freezer.
Mixture will not freeze solid, but to slush consistency.

title: chocolate rice pudding
directions: Mix rice, cocoa, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Chip up butter over the rice mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flavoring. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients with buttermilk.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: citrus lime muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Mix milk, eggs, oil, lime rind and lime juice in 2-cup measure.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir lightly with fork just until moist.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Spoon into muffin pan lined with papers 3/4 full. Bake for 20 minutes or until golden.

title: oriental omelet
directions: Beat eggs, cream and seasonings until thoroughly mixed.
Heat butter in skillet.
Pour in eggs and cook quickly, lifting edge of omelet so uncooked egg can drain under cooked portion.
When egg is almost done, add rice and roll omelet.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 325°. Test with toothpick.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt cheese in the milk in a double boiler.
Add the rest of the ingredients.

title: company chicken
directions: Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish and top with cheese.
Thin soup with water.
Mix until smooth and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix with melted butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or at 350° for 45 minutes (uncovered).

title: spiced sliced white potatoes
directions: Place oil and margarine in skillet, then add potatoes.
Place other ingredients in with potatoes.
Let cook slowly.
Stir in cheese last.
Add water if needed, stirring to keep ingredients from sticking.
Then cook until done (cover skillet with lid while cooking).

title: homemade play dough
directions: Cook on low heat, stirring continuously until a ball forms. Store in airtight container.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Add 2 cups mayonnaise and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix and spread over top of salad carefully.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: shortcake for strawberries
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients, blending until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch flat cake pan.
Bake until it springs back to the touch, approximately 20 minutes, at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add Wesson oil, carrots and eggs.
Pour into a baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt and stir together the margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Gently stir chocolate mix into cereal until well coated.
Put the confectioners sugar in a paper grocery bag.
Add chocolate coated cereal and shake until pieces are coated with sugar.
Store in an airtight container, if it doesn't all disappear!

title: waldorf astoria red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco with mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Add vanilla, flour with cocoa mixed into flour, alternating with buttermilk.
Pour in red food coloring.

title: chili sauce
directions: Tie spices in a piece of cheesecloth.
Chop all vegetables. Simmer together until mixture begins to thicken, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook, stirring often, until mixture becomes a thick sauce.
Remove spice bag.
Pack into sterile jars; seal.
Makes about 3 pints.

title: judy's rice casserole
directions: Cook the onion in the 3 tablespoons of butter until tender. Add the cooked rice, parsley, milk, and beaten eggs with 2 cups grated cheese.
Add seasonings.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: brownie s'mores
directions: Place brownies on microwave dish.
Arrange 3 candies on each brownie.
Microwave on High 10 to 15 seconds or just until chocolate candy begins to soften.
Top each brownie with Marshmallow Creme.
Microwave on High 10 to 15 seconds or just until Marshmallow Creme begins to soften.
Sprinkle with nuts. Makes 2 servings.

title: german honey bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix honey and sugar; add butter.
Sift and add 2 c. flour, enough to make a semi-liquid dough.
Add baking powder and soda, then almonds, peels and spices.
Then stir in 1 1/2-2 more c. flour.
Dough should now be sticky to the touch.

title: date loaf
directions: Put sugar, butter and milk in saucepan.
Cook at medium heat; stir well until soft ball stage.
Add nuts and dates; cook to soft ball stage again.
Add vanilla; beat until cool.
Pour into bowl lined with clean, damp cloth.
Cool completely and refrigerate. Cut into bite size pieces to serve.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add beaten eggs and melted butter.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with whipped cream.

title: brickle drizzles
directions: Combine 1 cup butter flavored Crisco, sugar and brown sugar in large bowl.
Stir until well blended and creamy.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt and soda and stir into creamy mixture.
Stir in oats.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Press tops into brickle chips.
Place brickle side up 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes; remove to cooling rack.

title: delicious plum bread
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray with flour for pan.

title: pea soup with pork(swedish cooking)
directions: Soak the peas in plenty of cold water for about 12 hours.
Add 1 tablespoon of salt perlitre (1 3/4 pints 4 1/4 cups) water. Place the pork knuckle in a pot with the water and bring to boil. Skim.
Peel and slice the onion; add it to the meat.
Cover and simmer on low heat about 1 hour.
Drain the peas and add them to the soup.
Cover and boil until the meat is tender and peas are soft, a further 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: clam chowder
directions: Put clams, onion, potatoes and tomatoes through food chopper. Put mixture with diced celery, salt, pepper, parsley and hot water in large cooker and start boiling.
Fry 1/2 pound bacon and onion together.
Add to the rest.
Cook slowly, stirring often.
When finished, cut 3 hard-boiled eggs into chowder.

title: orange-walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour (may use Pam) 6 mini loaf pan.
Mix flour, cornmeal and baking powder until thoroughly blended.
Set aside.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until fluffy.
Add eggs.

Beat 2 to 3 minutes longer, scraping down sides of bowl until mixture is very pale and increased in volume. With rubber spatula, alternately stir in flour mixture and milk, until smooth and well blended.
Stir in chopped nuts and orange and lemon peels.
Divide the batter equally into the prepared pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes, until tops are lightly browned and wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool completely.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan, pineapple and 1/2 cup water until it boils.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Let set on stove until cool.
When cool, add 2 cups buttermilk and stir well. Let set in refrigerator until thick.
Then fold in Cool Whip and cup of nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Gel.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat the water and juice to dissolve the gelatin and then add the cream cheese and blend in the other ingredients.
Whip the heavy cream and fold into the mixture.
Place into a mold and chill until firm.

title: italian seasoning
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and store in a tightly covered shaker container.
Use on meat, poultry, fish and vegetables. Makes 3/4 cup.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, water and coffee.
Bring to a boil.
After mixture has completely cooled, add vodka and put in half gallon jar. Add vanilla bean.
Let stand for 30 days, but turn each day.
Strain through cheesecloth after 30 days.
Enjoy!

title: raspberry-blueberry salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Add pineapple, pie filling and nuts (as you like).
Put in icebox to set.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: elaine's chocolate birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add 3 eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg. Add melted chocolate.
Sift 1/3 cup flour into batter.
Mix well and add 1/3 of the sour milk; mix slightly.
Repeat, ending with flour (secret - mix slightly).
Mix vanilla with boiling water; add to batter and mix.
Put in 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and lined with wax paper on bottom.
Pour batter into pans and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Fill large container of a propane cooker halfway with water; add 1/4 cup Old Bay seasoning.
Bring to a boil, following manufacturer's instructions.
Add potatoes, return to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Add sausage and corn; return to a boil and cook 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add shrimp; cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Remove with a slotted spoon onto a serving platter or newspaper-lined table.
Serve with additional Old Bay seasoning and cocktail sauce.
Yields 12 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, onion and garlic powder.
Chill.
Form into a ball.
Roll in nuts and chill.
May be frozen.

title: creamy spinach
directions: Cook frozen spinach in a small amount of water with onion until thawed.
Beat eggs and mix with remaining ingredients.
Add to the spinach and onions.
Bake in a greased casserole at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until center is set.
Do not overcook or it will separate.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry meringue pie
directions: Cook the sugar and water to a syrup.
Add the cranberries. Cook until berries pop.
Mix smoothly in a bowl the flour and egg yolks, then add the juice from the cranberries.
Add this mixture to the cooked berries and simmer for 3 minutes. Stir in the butter and vanilla.
Set aside and cool.
Turn filling into pie crust. Cover with meringue and brown.

title: tender beef roast
directions: Wash roast in cold water.
Sprinkle with all-purpose seasoning, salt and pepper on all sides.
Roll in flour.
Put in hot grease in large iron skillet and brown on both sides.
Put in roasting pan and sprinkle with more all-purpose seasoning.
Add 2 cups water and cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for each pound of meat or until tender.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and gradually add sugar, beating on medium speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating about 30 seconds after each addition.
Add flour to mixture alternately with whipping cream. Mix just blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put
yeast into 1/2 cup lukewarm water to soften.
Pour boiling
water
over
sugar,
shortening
and salt. Stir until dissolved. Add evaporated milk and beaten eggs. Stir well. Add yeast mixture
and mix again. Add the flour and stir thoroughly. Dough
will
be
sticky.
Chill in refrigerator with damp cloth covering
until
needed. Shape into rolls and let rise 2 hours. Bake
at 425° about 15 minutes.
(Will keep all week in refrigerator.)

title: meal in itself - baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger and onion; fry bacon and crumble. Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 hour. These beans are much better if you cook them in a crock-pot for about 6 hours on low.

title: party mix "trash"
directions: In saucepan over low heat, combine margarine, garlic salt, celery salt, onion powder and Worcestershire sauce.

title: dark sweet cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup cherry juice.
Add water, if needed.
Chill until it begins to thicken, then add sour cream.
Blend thoroughly.
Add cherries and nuts.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6.

title: chili dip
directions: Melt cheese with chili.
Serve with corn chips.

title: oven baked chicken wings
directions: *Available at Publix near spices in a round cardboard shaker container.

title: cinnamon cheese goodies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over crescent rolls.
If using pie filling, spread over cream cheese mixture.
Put another package of crescent rolls on top of filling.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Drizzle melted butter over top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Partially cook bacon; add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to clam juice to make 4 cups.
Add to bacon mixture.
Add tomatoes, potatoes, carrots and seasonings.
Cover and simmer about 35 minutes.
Blend flour with 2 tablespoons water to make a smooth paste.
Stir into chowder and cook, stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Add clams and heat through.
Add Tabasco to taste.

title: italian manicotti
directions: Saute meat, onion and green pepper. Drain off fat. Add tomato paste, water, salt, pepper, sugar and seasoning.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Parboil manicotti in salted water for 4 minutes. Drain on paper towels. Fill shells with combined cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Place shells in shallow greased baking dish. Cover with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked lima bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.
Stir once when uncovered.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar well. Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients together.
Add, alternating with sour cream, milk and flour mixture.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or may use Bundt pan, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peach easy dessert
directions: Arrange peaches on an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Sift together 1 cup flour, 2 tablespoons baking powder, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in 3 tablespoons butter until particles are fine.
Combine 1 slightly beaten egg and 1/4 cup milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches. Blend together 1 tablespoon butter, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit, except strawberries.
Mix in fruit cocktail, oranges and pineapple.
Pour in strawberries, with juice on top.
Then sprinkle instant pudding over top (do not stir). Let stand overnight.
Before serving, stir in bananas.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine all ingredients.
On foil, pat meat to a 10 x 18-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices atop meat, leaving room on the edges.
Reserve 2 slices of cheese.
Tear up remaining cheese; place over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift and seal edges and ends.
Place roll, seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/4 hours.
(Center will be pink due to ham.)
Slice cheese; melt approximately 2 minutes.

title: crab imperial(serves 4)
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease dish lightly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sausage and peppers
directions: Boil sausage 30 minutes.
In large skillet, brown garlic.
Add sliced peppers and sliced onions.
Saute until soft.
Partly cook potatoes.
Cut quarters and add to skillet.
Add stewed tomatoes. Salt and pepper.
Mix together.
Let cook 45 to 50 minutes on low flame.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together in frying pan.
Simmer on low (260°) until bubbly.
Serve with crackers in a chafing dish or fondue pot.

title: hoppy's irish creme liqueur
directions: Combine all in a blender.
Divide into gift bottles.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour boiled mixture over dry ingredients. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix all together and bake at 400° for 20 minutes in a shallow cookie sheet (11 x 17-inch) that has been greased and floured.

title: punch
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve jello.
Add sugar and mix.
Add lemonade and pineapple juice; add club soda last, just before serving.

title: petite artichoke pizzas
directions: Unroll dough without tearing.
Press into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except Parmesan.
Spread mixture on crust and sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes and cut into 2-inch squares.
Makes 36 appetizers.

title: easy strawberry jam
directions: Mix Sure-Jell and 1/4 cup of the sugar.
Add pectin mixture gradually to fruit, stirring vigorously.
Set aside for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir remaining sugar gradually into fruit mixture until sugar is completely dissolved and no longer grainy, about 3 minutes.
Pour into plastic containers. Cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.
Jam is now ready to use.
Store in refrigerate or freeze extra containers. Thaw in refrigerator.
Makes about 6 (1-cup) containers.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch skillet.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add milk.
Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat; cool.
Slowly add confectioners sugar, beating well after each addition, until thick enough to spread.

title: butter nut cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and eggs together for 10 minutes at high speed in mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat on high for 1 minute.
Add remaining flour and milk.
Beat 1 minute on high. Add butternut flavoring.
Beat well.
Pour in greased tube pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel frosted bars
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts, spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and spread with frosting.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Cover chicken with margarine.
Mix crackers, cheese and garlic into cracker mixture.
Cover well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake covered for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: german stew
directions: Brown pork chops and place in baking dish.
Peel and cut potatoes into wedges.
Place on top of pork chops.
Cover with mixed vegetables.
Season tomato sauce and cover vegetables. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Put vanilla wafers in paper lined muffin tins round side up. Beat ingredients together for 5 minutes.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling (cherry or blueberry).

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until butter melts.
Place chicken in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.
Serve over pasta or stuffing.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine baking mix, mustard and water in a small bowl and stir until dough forms.
With fingertips dipped in baking mix, press dough into bottom and up sides of prepared dish; set aside. Quarter hot dogs by cutting in half lengthwise and again crosswise.
Place hot dogs on dough.
Spoon chili over hot dogs. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate butterscotch fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.
In microwave-safe bowl, place butterscotch chips and 1/3 cup milk.
Set aside.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips and remaining milk and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 minute; stir until chips are melted.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread into prepared pan.
Microwave butterscotch chips on High 45 seconds; stir until chips are melted.
Spread evenly over chocolate layer.
Refrigerate until firm.
Remove from pan; peel off foil and cut into squares.
Makes about 4 dozen pieces; store in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients. Start in crock-pot on high. When mixture starts to cook, turn to medium or low until desired consistency, possibly 24 hours or more. Stir off bottom with a spatula. Add 1/2 teaspoon oil toward the end.

title: cheese ball
directions: Bring cream cheese to room temperature and combine with remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Refrigerate overnight. Shape into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: banana oat muffins
directions: Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Combine bananas, buttermilk, oil and egg whites.
Mix well with wire whip.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix.
Put sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake in oven at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 3 grams fat and 110 calories.

title: quesadillas
directions: Shred cheese and chop peppers, if not already diced.
Heat oil in skillet.
Place cheese and chiles on each tortilla and fold in half.
Secure with toothpick, if desired.
Fry, turning once, until tortilla is golden brown on both sides.

title: sherried chicken with peas
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
In a large frying pan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter/margarine over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook, stirring constantly until opaque, about 3 minutes.
Add scallions and mushrooms and cook 2 minutes.
Add sherry, peas and broth.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 20 minutes.

title: green bean supreme
directions: Cook onion and parsley in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and lemon peel.
Add sour cream and mix well.
Stir in drained beans.
Heat and stir.
Turn into baking dish.
Top with cheese.

title: chili con queso
directions: Brown onion. Add sausage. Cook and drain.
Add taco sauce and simmer. Cut cheese in cubes and melt.
Add chilies and other ingredients. Best if kept in crock-pot so cheese does not harden. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in top of double boiler.
Add milk slowly, mixing well.
Cook over moderate heat until thickened.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks; cook 3 minutes longer.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; stir well.
Let cool for 5 minutes.
Pour into baked crust.
Cover with meringue or whipped topping.
Chill well before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and chopped onions in skillet over medium heat until cooked.
Drain grease and leave in skillet. Add beans and remaining ingredients and cook until hot.
Serves 6.

title: ice  water chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift and add alternately with ice water, flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Melt squares of chocolate.
Add to batter and bake in a 350° oven until cake springs back when touched in the middle.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in foil-lined broiler pan.
Use enough foil to fold over and cover ingredients.
Add to roast remainder of ingredients. Pour soup over all.
Fold over foil and seal tightly.
Bake at 350° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: pear relish
directions: Mix in order given and cook over low heat until thick.
Seal in hot jars. Store in a dark place. Some cooks like to mix 1/2 cup plain flour with some of the saved pear juice and make a thin paste.
Stir this into the mixture after it is done. This will cut cooking time. Be sure to cook until the relish is thick in either case.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and add oil.
Add sugar, brown sugar, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, salt and crushed pineapple; add to zucchini mixture and stir until well blended.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: basic tomato-noodle recipe
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Add cheese and tomatoes; stir well. Serve.
Can add whatever other ingredients you have around the kitchen.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, onion and egg in separate bowl.
Layer macaroni, soup mixture and cheese in alternate layers.
Melt margarine and add crushed Cheese Nips. Sprinkle this on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut up and cook potatoes and eggs.
Add salad cubes, potatoes and eggs; toss lightly.
Add mustard, mayonnaise and celery seed to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: golden chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut into small pieces.
Boil spaghetti in chicken broth.
Saute onion and bell pepper in butter. Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: super snack bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and eggs in large bowl until well blended.
Stir in flour, cereal, 3/4 cup pecans, 2/3 cup of candies, the oats, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Spread in ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches. Sprinkle with remaining pecans and candies.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars about 2 x 1 1/4-inches.
Makes 32 bars.

title: kielbasa and cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, combine cabbage, onion and kielbasa. Cover.
Cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes until cabbage and onions are soft and clear.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through. Makes 4 servings.

title: gina's cheese ball
directions: Cut dried beef into small pieces.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing and dried chipped beef together.
Make into log or ball and roll in pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: pizza bread
directions: Brown ground beef and add spaghetti sauce.
Slice French bread longways in half.
Add a layer of sauce mixture, then add a layer of each cheese and bake at 350° until cheeses are melted or bread is as crispy as you would like.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Saute onion in 2 Tbsp. butter and let cool.
Rub bowl with garlic; mix meat, salt, pepper and onion.
Add rice and parsley. Core cabbage, place in large pot and pour hot water over cabbage to soften leaves.
Let stand in hot water for 10 minutes.
Remove from water, cut out hearts and cross ends of cabbage leaves over each other.
Place 1/4 c. meat mixture onto leaf, roll up and tuck in edges.
Spread 1 lb. sauerkraut into bottom of large pan and place stuffed cabbage leaves on top of sauerkraut.
Cover with remaining sauerkraut, pour tomato sauce over sauerkraut and add enough water to cover pigs.
Add salt & pepper.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for about 1 1/2 hours.
Melt 1 Tbsp. butter; add flour and stir until flour is brown.
Stir browned flour into sauerkraut/water mix.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: green jello salad
directions: Stir together Jell-O and boiling water; dissolve.
Cool to egg white consistency.
Beat in condensed milk and Miracle Whip.
Fold in cottage cheese, pineapple and pecans.
Chill and garnish with cherries and mint leaves.

title: shrimp cocktail sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients; store in refrigerator.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, dry Jell-O and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Mix graham crackers, milk and oleo.
Add bits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: nugget cream spinach
directions: Saute onion, garlic, bacon, salt and pepper in butter.
Add flour and cook until smooth roux; slowly add milk and cook until thick.
Chop frozen spinach very fine.
Squeeze all water out. Add spinach to sauce; bring to a slow boil and cook 5 minutes.

title: grand marnier candied apple and orange tart
directions: Arrange apples in concentric circles in the tart shell; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of sugar and dot with butter.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 50 minutes to one hour, or until apples are tender and golden.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining sugar, 1/3 cup Grand Marnier and 1/3 cup water; bring to a boil and simmer until clear.
Off heat, add orange sections and let cool.
Arrange orange sections between apple slices in tart shell. Reduce cooking liquid to 1/4 cup; add preserves and reserved Grand Marnier and simmer for 5 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes and spoon over the tart.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix and pour cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix the 2 eggs, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together.
Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: mama's dried apple cake
directions: Cream butter or Crisco and sugar.
Add flour sifted with soda and baking powder alternately with buttermilk and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in layers at 325° for about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: granny's rice casserole
directions: Place raw rice in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add drained mushrooms.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Melt butter in pan.
Add pieces of chicken then spread cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix stuffing according to package (add all ingredients).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: german slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, onions and bell pepper.
Mix together next 4 ingredients and boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep seven days.
May add 1 grated carrot also.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Chill milk.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Chill until partially set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Add lemon juice and sugar.
Whip chilled milk and fold into jello mixture.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbs.
Pour jello mixture over top.
Put remaining crumbs on top and chill until firm.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti.
Brown beef.
Drain ziti.
Stir in salt.
Mix egg with Ricotta, Parmesan and beef.
Add half the spaghetti sauce and toss to coat ziti.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish or lasagne pan.
Pour remaining sauce over the top and sprinkle with the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: In a pan, cook the vinegar, water and salt to a rolling boil. Put pickles in jar.
Pour solution over pickles.
Add dill seed, garlic gloves and alum to each jar.
Put seals and rings on jars. Place in boiling water bath; process for 5 minutes.
Ready to eat in 6 weeks.
Allows time for ingredients to mix well.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: spicy beef and cabbage soup
directions: Brown beef.
Drain off most of fat.
Add chopped onions and celery.
Saute all until soft.
Add both cans of tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste.
Cook a few minutes and add water, cabbage and chili powder.
Cook 1 hour and add kidney beans.
Cook over low heat for an hour longer.
I add about 1 teaspoon baking soda after the beans.
It cuts the acidity in tomatoes and makes beans easier to digest without affecting the taste.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix
sugar,
syrup
and
water
together and cook until mixture
turns
a long thread from the spoon.
Add peanuts and stir constantly until syrup mixture turns light brown in color and peanuts are done.
Add salt, butter and soda.
Stir until thoroughly
mixed and pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Spread as thin as possible and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tarheel breakfast
directions: Fry bacon.
Mix flour and buttermilk in bowl until combined. Add shortening until flour feels like cornmeal.
Add water a dash at a time until dough is rollable.
Roll onto floured surface and cut circles with glass to make biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown (10 to 15 minutes).
Remove bacon.
Place flour into drippings; brown until clumpy.
Add enough milk to thicken.
Fry eggs.
Serve with hot biscuits and gravy with crumbled bacon on top.

title: rice salad
directions: Toss everything except cucumber.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well, chill and serve with vegetables.

title: elsie's jello salad
directions: Heat orange juice and dissolve jello.
Let cool slightly.
Mix in grated carrots, apples and pineapple.
Set in refrigerator until almost congealed.
Add whipped topping, nuts and marshmallows.
Make the day before serving.

title: stuffless cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain any fat.
Spread half of cabbage in a greased casserole.
Spread ground beef mixture on cabbage, then sprinkle rice over meat.
Add the rest of the cabbage and the salt and pepper.
Combine the tomato soup and water.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° covered for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes to brown top slightly.
May be served with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: mediterranean sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on bread (cocktail rye). Spray cookie sheet; bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes until melted or toasted brown.

title: banana oatmeal bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray loaf pan with Pam and coat with 1
teaspoon
all-purpose flour.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Combine
rest
of ingredients and stir until moist. Pour in loaf pan
and
bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: sunshine casserole
directions: Boil water (about twice the amount of macaroni you use).
Add 3 chicken bouillon cubes; let macaroni get tender and add Cheez Whiz (according to how cheesy you want it).
After it has cooked, add a little cream.
Do not add salt.
Add pepper, if desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and rinse the pasta.
Chop pepper and cucumber and slice cherry tomatoes in halves.
Drain olives.
Mix all ingredients except dressing.
Mix them thoroughly, then add dressing of your choice, enough to coat the salad good.
Chill for about 1 hour and serve.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder; stir.
Cut in shortening.
Gradually stir in water and mix well.

title: mom's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together the sugar and milk and boil until a soft ball forms. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients until well mixed. Spread in a greased pan.

title: creamy fettuccine with veggies
directions: Cook pasta, steam veggies.
Puree in blender cottage cheese, milk, basil, parsley.
Combine veggies and pasta.
Pour sauce over and serve room temperature or hot.

title: quiche
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes and then at 350° for 15 minutes.
(Put foil around edge of crust during last 15 minutes to keep from getting too brown.)

title: apple and ? pie filling crisp
directions: Cut apples with peelings on into pieces or slices and top with 1/2 can pie filling of your choice.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Prepare in 1-quart Tupperware casserole.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
By hand is best.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: calamondin marmalade
directions: Wash fruit; cut into halves, remove seeds and slice thinly or put through food chopper.
For each cup of fruit add 3 cups water. Bring to a boil.
Cook 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Mix and stir in sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Mix in rhubarb.
Spray dish or grease.
Dot top of mixture with butter.
Bake about 1 hour at 400°.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar and salt.
Chill.
When slightly thickened, add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Turn into individual molds.
Place in the refrigerator until firm.
When ready to serve, unmold on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with mayonnaise.
Serves 6.
May be served from one large mold or bowl.

title: chocolate delight ice cream squares
directions: Allow ice cream to soften in large mixing bowl. Break up cookies into very small pieces (not fine crumbs) in plastic bag with rolling pin. Stir into softened ice cream. Fold in thawed whipped topping. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan and freeze. Cut into 2 inch squares when ready to serve.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix last 5 ingredients and stir with crackers.
Store in covered container.
Stir until crackers are dry, off and on for 3 hours.

title: homemade stickers
directions: Has 6 easy steps. magazine/newspaper/old book or any shape you wish. part vinegar. cut-out shape, making sure edges are covered. clear). greeting cards, anything the child wishes to decorate.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake in 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients; spread over hot baked layer and bake 20 minutes longer.
Cool, cut into bars 3 x 1-inch long.

title: pie crust
directions: Add flour with baking powder; mix in shortening with pastry blender.
Add cold water; blend only until moistened.
Roll out. Makes top and bottom crust.

title: chocolate peanut butter delights
directions: Mix peanut butter, brown sugar, confectioners sugar and 4 tablespoons of softened butter or margarine.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the melted chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons softened butter or margarine together; spread over the top of the peanut butter mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheery cherry pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine cooked rotini, cherries, cucumbers, carrots and onions; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine salad dressing, lemon juice, dill weed and pepper.
Pour dressing mixture over pasta, tossing to coat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken pastel
directions: Dress and bone the chicken.
Cut into small pieces and place in a bowl.
Squeeze the lemon into the chicken and add the toyo. Let stand for 15 minutes.
Put in a saucepan with water and salt and pepper to taste; simmer until the meat is tender and most of the liquid has evaporated.
Slice the hard-boiled eggs, Vienna sausage and chorizo.
Fry the cooked chicken and chorizo in butter until brown.

title: christmas scent(not edible)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tea kettle or saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer as long as desired for a Christmasy-smelling house.
Check often and add water if needed. May be stored in refrigerator for several days and reused.

title: bill's fat noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, breaking it up into small pieces.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
In a large casserole dish, put both soups and stir to get out lumps.
Add corn with juice (if you use regular corn instead of the Niblets, drain off most of the juice).
Stir in the hamburger and noodles when they are ready. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bailey's irish creme liquor
directions: Put all in a blender. Mix. Refrigerate at least 24 hours and bottle.

title: mexican velveeta dip
directions: Saute tomatoes and onion.
Add chilies.
Mix together all ingredients and serve warm.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Combine and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch buttered pan or dish as you would a graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool thoroughly.

title: holubky(slovak stuffed cabbage)
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg and seasonings.
Core cabbage and parboil about 20 minutes, covered.
Separate leaves, when cool; stuff with meat mixture and roll up.

In large kettle, place a layer of sauerkraut, then a layer of cabbage rolls, then a layer of tomatoes, then pieces of pork shoulder, seasoning as you go. When all is used, cover to the top of the kettle with boiling water and cook over medium heat about 2 1/2 hours.

title: delicious hush puppies
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add oil and milk.
Stir well.
Cover and let set for 2 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls in hot oil.
Hush Puppies will float when done.

title: cherry torte
directions: Beat egg whites; add cream of tartar, then sugar slowly.
Add vanilla.
Break crackers with hands.
Fold crackers and chopped nuts into egg whites.
Put into greased 9 x 12-inch or 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with Dream Whip, then spoon on ready prepared pie filling cherries.
Put into refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: hot cranberry casserole
directions: Place cranberries in casserole dish and layer apples on top. Mix remaining ingredients; spread over top of fruit.
Bake at 350° until brown.
This is a good side dish for Thanksgiving or Christmas.

title: california burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except last three) in large bowl.
Form into patties.
Grill, broil or saute.
Serve on rolls with lettuce and tomato.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate cream pie(sugar-free)
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Mix into pudding mix the cream cheese (add milk if needed).
Then add 1 3/4 cups milk, sweetener and Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put into two custard cups.
Sprinkle water over apple slices.
Mix all other ingridents until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes two servings.

title: chilled cocktail appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill thoroughly. Serves 6.

title: dress up that macaroni and cheese
directions: You have a choice of dressing up your macaroni and cheese either Italian style, Mexican style, or tuna style.
Prepare macaroni and cheese using instructions on the package. Stir in your choice of dress up ingredients; tomate sauce and Italian seasoning OR canned chili OR tuna and pimentos.
Let set for a few minutes to blend flavors.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water about 5 minutes. Add soda and let cool. Cream sugars and shortening. Add eggs. Beat well. Add the cooled raisin mixture, oatmeal, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, nut meats and flour. Mix well. Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: parmesan squash toss
directions: Slice zucchini and yellow squash diagonally (use a crinkle cutter if you have one).
Saute vegetables in olive oil in a large skillet over medium high heat 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients; toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: pea bean salad
directions: Mix peas, peanuts, cheese and onion; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to pea and cheese mixture; chill.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Combine crumbs, cheese and a dash of black pepper.
Dip chicken in egg, then coat with crumbs.
Place in baking dish sprayed with Pam and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes more.
Heat sauce and pour over; top with cheese.
Return to oven to melt.
Serve over pasta.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and peanut butter and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add cereal.
Stir until coated.
Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips in microwave; spread over cereal mixture.

title: red punch for all
directions: Mix cranberry juice, orange juice and pineapple juice.
Chill well.
Just before serving, add Sprite.
May be garnished with dips of sherbet or an ice ring.

title: chili dip
directions: In a glass Pyrex cake dish, layer in order, making sure the cheese is spread evenly.
Bake at 350° until top cheese is melted. Serve with large Fritos or scoop Fritos.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda together; set aside.
Mix shortening and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Alternate flour mixture with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Mash bananas and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or two 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks.
Add 1/2 cup of lemon juice to yolks slowly.
Add sweetened condensed milk. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Put into a big bowl and mix the first 3 ingredients.
Put into another bowl the next 4 ingredients.
Add flour mixture to first bowl.
Mix well.
Dough should be soft and easy to handle.
Add a tablespoon of flour if dough is too sticky.
Combine in a small dish and set aside the 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Roll dough into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture. Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 3 cookies across and 5 down.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.
Don't overbake!
Cookies should be soft and puffy.
Cool on rack.
Makes 3 dozen.
Eat warm with a glass of milk.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and pecans.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Put pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° or 400° for 8 to 15 minutes.

title: eight cup cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and oil. Add egg.
Beat well. Add rest of ingredients.
Shape into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix Jell-O, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Let boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Place sliced strawberries in baked pie shell. Pour cooled filling over berries.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Add whipped topping just before serving, if desired.

title: homemade carrot cake
directions: Mix salad oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, vanilla, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, pineapple, walnuts, raisins, coconut and carrots.
Mix together and add flour.
Mix.
Pour into a 10-inch well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° until brown.
Stick a toothpick in cake; if it comes out clean, it is done. Cool.
Ice with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple chunks, cheese, sugar, juice and flour together.
Spray casserole dish with Pam and add pineapple mixture.
Mix crackers and melted butter together and put on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Pour envelope of soup mix into sour cream.
Mix well.
Let set for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Great with chips.

title: divinity
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil until it cracks as it cooks and will stand like an icicle when dropped in cold water.
I beat my egg whites while candy is cooking. Pour the sugar mixture over the egg whites and beat until it stands in peaks in bowl.
Dip by spoonful and place on waxed paper.
Nuts or coconut (1/2 cup) may be added just before time to cool.

title: broken glass salad
directions: Dissolve lime, orange and strawberry Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water (separately).
Pour into pans and let it set.
Heat the pineapple juice, sugar and water to boiling point.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in that.
Let set until slightly jelled, then whip it and fold Cool Whip in.
Cut the lime, orange and strawberry Jell-O into squares and fold into mixture.
Put into bowl and let it set.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bake puff pastries according to package directions.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and lemon juice until smooth and creamy. When pastries are done, remove from oven and let cool slightly, then cut in half.
Layer cream cheese mixture and canned pie filling on each, then replace top and drizzle a little more pie filling on top.
Top with whipped cream if desired and serve.

title: refrigerator cookies
directions: Work into
small
rolls.
Let stand overnight or longer in refrigerator.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: yogurt mini muffins
directions: You will also need nonstick cooking spray.

title: potato sandwich buns
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and potatoes in bowl with salt.
Beat with fork.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Stir in yeast and water.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups flour.
Mix well.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour (enough to make dough stiff).
Mix well.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and make buns.
(Form like hamburger patties.)
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: best ever carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Stir in carrots. Add oil, eggs and vanilla. Blend well. Bake in 3 greased and floured round pans for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: "new jersey" chili
directions: Brown and drain chopped meat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.
Stir occasionally.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Add water to dates and let stand.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cocoa.
Set aside.

title: potato water sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast	and
sugar
in portion of potato water. Combine all ingredients in large glass bowl.
Cover with cloth and let stand
at
room
temperature for 24 to 48 hours.
Stir occasionally.
When
bubbly and a nice yeasty odor, starter is ready.

title: cajun marinade
directions: Mix.
Marinate about 1 pound of shrimp or 1 pound of chicken for 1 hour and grill.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Mix everything together, except cheese; pour into a large casserole (9 x 13-inches). Grate cheese over top and cover with foil; refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except jello and strawberries) on stove. Stir until thick.
Add jello.
Pour over strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: mushroom in garlic sauce
directions: Combine olive oil and garlic.
Saute.
Stir in flour.
Saute. Add broth gradually.
Stir until smooth.
Add parsley, lemon juice and red chilies. Stir well to thicken.
Add mushrooms. Stir in and heat for about 5 minutes or until done. Serve hot.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Lay sheet of pastry on bottom of pan.
Pour in pie filling and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Cut second pastry sheet into strips and weave top crust. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put several pats of butter around on top. Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: pineapple casserole(stuffing)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except
bread
and butter.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over
bread and toss.
Mix bread with pineapple mixture and pour
into buttered baking dish and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 425°.
Can
be
baked at 350° for about 45 minutes if something else is
in the oven baking.
Serves 4 to 6.
Great with ham.

title: applestick snack
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine juice and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin and stir until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Add apple.
Chill until set, about 2 hours.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Soak together for 1 hour the rolled oats and sour milk.
Mix together well the shortening, egg and brown sugar.
Sift together soda, salt, flour and baking powder.
Stir in with oats and milk. Fill tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, shortening, and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth. combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and flavoring mix well.
Add coconut and nuts. mix well. Gently fold in beaten egg whites with a wooden spoon.
Grease and flour three 9 inch cake pans.
Pour batter in.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let Cool.

title: meatballs and sauce
directions: Mix soup, milk and sauce together.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes. Add ground beef.
Mix together and form meatballs.
Broil for 10 to 12 minutes, turning, on both sides.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Prepare spinach as directed in Step 1 of Spanakaopita Peloponnisos recipe. Gently fry onion in oil for 10 minutes.
Add spring onion and fry for further 5 minutes.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Select small firm green tomatoes and pack into sterilized jars. To each quart, add 1 clove of garlic, 1 stalk of celery, 1 hot pepper and 1 head of dill.

title: butter bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Rinse with cool water; drain well.
In a bowl, mix beans with oil, lemon juice, parsley, sliced green onions, tomatoes and enough pepper to make salad slightly hot to taste. If made ahead, cover and chill up to 4 hours, then mix.
Crumble cheese onto salad.
Garnish with whole onions.

title: quick pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into the pie shell. Bake until done.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together cocoa, butter, sugar and milk.
Boil 1 minute. Take off stove.
Add oatmeal; add vanilla.
Add peanut butter (in that order).
Mix together.
Drop cookies on wax paper.
Takes 1/2 hour to cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine
butter and boiling water.
Stir until shortening
is melted.
Combine
eggs, sugar and salt.
Beat in cold water. Soften
yeast
in
lukewarm water.
Combine 3 mixtures and add flour.
Cover and chill overnight.
Shape and let rise and bake as for standard rolls.
Makes 36.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: moon craters
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a gooey rock mixture.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift together dry
ingredients.
Beat egg slightly; add milk, and stir
into
first
mixture.
Add
melted shortening. For deep frying, dip wieners in batter, holding with a fork or skewer. Drain excess batter over bowl.
Fry at 375° in a wire basket until golden
brown.
Drain
on absorbent paper.	Serve hot.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift flour, measure and resift with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add mashed banana, sour cream and chopped nuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put frozen hash brown potatoes out to thaw well ahead of time. Mix potatoes and the remaining ingredients, except the Ritz crackers.
Pour this mixture into a well-buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle the crushed Ritz crackers over the top.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Grease pan.
In bowl, mix rice, celery soup, chicken soup and water.
Pour in pan; lay chicken on top and sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours, covered with foil.
Uncover last 20 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad(serves 8)
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Cover with topping. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pina colada
directions: Best mixed in blender, adding shake mix last.

title: meatballs
directions: In butter or margarine, fry onions and bell peppers until tender.
Mix in all other ingredients and pour over meatballs. Heat in a 350° oven about 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and soda.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add yeast and milk.
Roll and cut into biscuits and bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In the top of a double boiler, stir together the brown sugar, salt, light cream and 2 egg yolks, slightly beaten.
