Cook the mixture over gently boiling water, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Add butter and vanilla.	Cool the sauce before serving.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Combine hamburger meat, sausage, soup mix, onion, celery, water and green pepper.
Cook in pan on top of stove for 20 minutes.
Add remaining 1/2 cup water, soy sauce, mushrooms and rice.
Put in baking dish and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: kart wheels
directions: Heat the oven to 375°.
Mix flour, margarine, powdered sugar and baking powder and just enough milk until dough forms.
Divide the dough into 6 equal parts.
Shape each part into a ball.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Make an indentation 1 3/4-inches in diameter and about 3/4-inch deep in center of each flattened ball.
Fill each indentation with about 2 tablespoons of pie filling.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 Kart Wheels.

title: oven dressing
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown meat and pour off grease.
Slowly melt cheese, cut in chunks.
Put in crock-pot.
After cheese has melted, add meat, Ro-Tel and milk.
Stir.
Very good with your favorite chips.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter together.
Then add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour, milk and drained pineapple alternately.
Place in a cool oven.
Start at 325°, 1 1/2 hours. Let cool about 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: beef pie
directions: Cut beef in small pieces; brown in butter.
Cook onion until tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add mushrooms.
In separate pan, pour beef consomme and thicken with cornstarch; pour in a little sherry.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Line with puffy pastry.
Beat up egg with a little water; coat pastry.
Place beef, etc. in pastry; cover with another piece of pastry.
Brush with egg and bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 30 minutes.
Great dish!

title: pocatello potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cool potatoes with jackets on.
Dice potatoes, leaving some peeling.
Cube cheese and sprinkle on top. Simmer onions in butter 5 minutes.
Add to potatoes with pimentos, bread cubes, onion salt, garlic salt and parsley.
Toss.
Spread into baking dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and bubbles (about 30 minutes).

title: baked lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Baste frequently. Serve with hot cooked rice.

title: cumin rice
directions: Saute onion, pepper and rice in bacon drippings.
Add consomme, Worcestershire, salt and cumin seed.
Bring to a boil, stir and cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook 20 minutes.

title: banana bread(not too sweet.)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy; add egg and beat well.
Add mashed bananas.
Stir in dry ingredients slowly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: something different sweet rolls
directions: Mix the cake mix, yeast and flour together well.
Stir in hot water.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Roll into a rectangle on floured surface.
Spread with softened margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Roll jelly roll style.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch slices.
Place on a greased baking pan (2 inches deep).
Let rise until double.
Add topping.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into bite size balls.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: dip for fritos or tortilla chips
directions: Mix together refried beans and picante sauce.
Melt cheese and add to other mixture.
Keep warm.

title: quick and easy vegetable soup(serves 6)
directions: In large pot, saute onion in margarine.
Add ground beef and brown.
Add vegetables and V-8 juice.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for about 15 minutes.

title: quick n easy fudge (peanut butter)
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, salt and the 1/2 cup milk. Bring to a boil, and boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Pour into greased 9x9-inch pan and allow to cool.

title: harvard beets
directions: Prepare beets.
Cut off all but 1 inch of beet tops.
Wash beets and leave whole with root ends attached.
Pierce each beet with a knife.
Place beets and 1/2 cup of water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and microwave on High for 18 to 25 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes until tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Run cold water over beets; slip off skin and remove root ends.
Slice beets.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into jello until dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon.
Pour 2 cups of gelatin into bowl. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours until thick.
Reserve 1 cup at room temperature.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls flat on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients together as you would a meat loaf.
Divide into 2 portions.
Roll out in sausage shape and wrap in Handi-Wrap.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in a pan up on a rack.

title: heavenly shrimp boat
directions: Place shrimp in saucepan with water.
Boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Mix together shrimp, mayonnaise, celery and onion. Season to taste with salt, Worcestershire sauce, white pepper, dry mustard and lemon juice.
Spread mixture onto open buns and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle a dash of paprika over cheese for color.
Place these shrimp boats onto a cookie sheet and bake at 400° until golden brown, only takes a few minutes.

title: baked victorian french toast
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine and light corn syrup in a small saucepan, just until margarine is melted. Pour mixture into 13X9 pan. Arrange bread slices in a single layer, but snugly packed on top of caramel syrup. In medium bowl mix, eggs, milk, cinnamon until well blended. Pour over bread in baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove cover. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. or until center appears set and top is slightly brown. Let stand about 10 minutes before serving. Serve two slices on plate topped with fresh fruit and whipped cream or powdered sugar.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar.
Alternate flour and eggs; stir well.
Add vanilla and nuts; stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan lined with foil or well-greased.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: tara-tour sauce (tahini sauce)
directions: Pound garlic with salt.
Add tahini and lemon juice.
Mix until smooth.
Serve over warm fish or steamed vegetables.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: In a large bowl or casserole dish, combine Velveeta, salsa and sausage.
Cook eggs (do not add salt) in lightly oiled skillet. Add eggs to cheese mixture.
Warm flour tortillas according to package.
Place four or five tablespoons of mixture in each tortilla and roll up.
Place on platter; serve with extra salsa and sour cream.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cheese and cream together; chill.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple chunks, cantaloupe, etc.

title: aunt t's pecan pralines
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and slowly bring to a full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Do not let milk scorch.
Boil 2 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, add pecans and vanilla.
Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop level tablespoonfuls onto wax paper or foil.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: pralines(this is a good old fashioned recipe.)
directions: In a large pan, mix together all ingredients, except the pecans.
Cook to a soft ball.
(Use candy thermometer.) Cool.
Add chopped pecans and beat hard until mixture is stiff and creamy. When stiff, drop with a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet about 4-inches in diameter.
Press whole pecans on top of each one. Wrap pralines in oiled or waxed paper.

title: banana split pie
directions: Prepare pudding.
Pour into crust.
Slice bananas over pudding.
Put pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with cherries and chopped nuts.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise; spread over 12-inch pizza pan.
Scatter shrimp on cheese layer.
Cover with seafood sauce.
Then layer on the shredded cheese, green pepper, onion and tomato.
Cover and chill until serving time. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: three week slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, bell pepper and 2 cups sugar together and let stand while preparing next part.
Mix vegetable oil, vinegar, celery seed, salt and 1/2 cup sugar to a boil.
While hot, pour over cabbage mixture and stir.
Refrigerate and stir a couple of times.
Better if made a day ahead of time to be used.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add vanilla.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.
Top with strawberries and glaze.
Refrigerate any leftovers.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all in a bowl.
Pour into a lightly greased pie dish and bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes own crust.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon in boiling water.
Combine bouillon, egg and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 6-inch loaf.
Bake in lightly greased pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crumbly topped rhubarb
directions: Combine the rhubarb, flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a 10 x 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add 1 tablespoon of water and cream together. Set aside.

title: lazarus bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mince garlic in blender, using Port wine for liquid.
Add mayonnaise, tarragon and buttermilk.
Blend on low speed.
Fold in Bleu cheese.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar at high speed until it forms soft mounds.
Gradually add sugar, continuing to beat.
Beat 3 more minutes or until it forms stiff peaks.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut and trim round steak into serving size pieces.
Wipe with paper towels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour a little olive oil in bottom of a heavy pot.
Brown meat, uncovered, on both sides.
After meat is browned, remove.
Under low heat, saute onions and green peppers.
Add a clove of garlic.
(May add celery also.)
When vegetables are limp, add a can of tomato sauce, instant soup mix and 2 cans of water.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Meat will be "fork tender."
(Add water, if sauce cooks down.)

title: strawberry icing
directions: Combine the butter and confectioners sugar and mix with beater until blended and smooth.
Add the berry juice a bit at a time until
the
desired
spreading consistency is reached. Frost the Simple Strawberry Cake.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar thoroughly.
Let stand while you mix the other ingredients in a large enough bowl to hold the entire mixture.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt, soda and spices alternately with sugar-apple mixture. Pour into well oiled and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Fold (don't beat) the first 4 ingredients together.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
Sprinkle crumbled wafers on top.

title: fruit smoothieceres, california
directions: Combine orange juice, strawberries, skim milk, water and honey in blender.
Blend on high speed until smooth - about 1 minute.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread cream of chicken soup over bottom 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir sour cream with soup a little.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Place cheese on top of chicken.
Cover and return to oven.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cover with Stove Top dressing out of can.
Bake 10 minutes uncovered.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cook chocolate and milk until they boil.
Let mixture cool; beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Add chocolate mixture and add flour (sifted with baking powder).
Add vanilla and bake in 2 (9-inch) pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool on racks.

title: cocoons
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 275° for 50 minutes.
Dip in powdered sugar.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute the onion, garlic and carrot over medium heat until soft and golden brown.
Add tomatoes, parsley, oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Partially cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: "scrump-de'li-cious" cranberry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O; after Jell-O is set, whip until fluffy.
Stir sugar and crushed pineapple into cranberries, walnuts, oranges, celery, apples and grapes.
Stir fruit mixture into Jell-O. Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Thirty minutes before serving, fold in whipped cream and marshmallows.

title: fried green onions
directions: Place grease in skillet; heat.
Cut onions in 1-inch pieces. Pour in skillet.
Add salt and fry until onions are wilted.

title: mrs. bryant's yellow rice and chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; brown in skillet in small amount of olive oil.
Place chicken in large roaster.
Sprinkle celery, pepper, onion, garlic and pimento (and peas) over chicken.
Add rice and water.
Float 1 saffron thread at a time over casserole until all are used.
Cover; cook in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with Cuban bread and green salad.

title: shrimp mousse(excellent for open house)
directions: Cream sour cream, mayonnaise and cream cheese together in bowl. Add shrimp, vegetables, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce and salt; mix well.
Soften gelatin in shrimp water and lemon juice in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until dissolved.
Add to cream cheese/shrimp mixture; mix well.
Pour into large mold; chill until firm.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Season cleaned shrimp well with seasoned salt and lemon pepper.
Toss shrimp with melted oleo.
Lay in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine cheese and potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple cream cheese salad
directions: Make jello according to directions on package.
When starting to thicken, whip in cream cheese.
Then add pineapple.
Put in mold.

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a slow boil. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Note:
You can buy the green can of broken shrimp.
It is cheaper and shrimp will break anyway.

title: mini reubens
directions: Place rye bread (buttered on bottom side) on cookie sheet. Add a layer of corned beef. Saute sauerkraut in butter.
Layer sauerkraut over corned beef. Add dressing now, if desired. Top with sauerkraut.
Bake until cheese melts and is lightly browned. Makes approximately 40.

title: my best fruitcake
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add dates, nuts and fruit; stir to coat well.
Combine eggs and vanilla.
Mix into flour nut mixture.
Spoon into loaf pans (2 large or 4 mini).
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and peanut butter. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into shell and chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: almond brickle chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased glass baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes; let cool.

title: spinach hummus
directions: Place garlic and green onion in food processor with metal blade.
Process until minced.
Add drained garbanzo beans and puree until smooth.
Add spinach, lemon juice, water, tahini paste and salt.
Process until mixed.

title: zesty mozzarella chicken
directions: Combine egg white and milk.
In another bowl, mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Dip each chicken breast in the egg mixture, then in the crumb mixture.

title: banana nut ice cream
directions: Add sugar slowly to beaten eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into freezer and finish filling container with milk.

title: peas and corn casserole
directions: Pour juice off peas and corn.
Pour into casserole dish.
Add soup.
In pan melt 1/2 stick butter; crumble in crackers until all the liquid is absorbed.
Spread over top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place peanuts and sugar in syrup in a glass bowl.
Stir. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Take out, stir well and microwave 4 more minutes.
Take out, add margarine, stir well and microwave 2 more minutes.
Take out; add vanilla and soda.
Mix well.
Pour onto buttered sheet of foil.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: scrumptious meat balls
directions: Mix meats in
a large bowl.
Put in eggs.
Add salt and pepper.
Add
garlic
salt,
oregano
and
parsley.
Add bread crumbs.
Soak
bread
in
warm water, squeeze excess water and put in with meat mix.
If too soupy, add bread crumbs.
If too dry, add milk or olive oil.
Mold into meatballs.
Do not fry, just add meatballs to sauce.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie crust (have edges crimped high because amount of filling is generous).
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Boil green tomatoes and sugar for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add jello and mix thoroughly.
Boil another 5 minutes.
Pour into pint jars and process in water bath canner for 35 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut out stems of peppers and remove seeds.
Boil peppers for 5 minutes in salted water; drain and set aside.
Heat oil.
Put celery, onion and ground turkey in skillet.
Saute celery and onion, being careful not to burn.
Brown the turkey.
Add the rice, sauce and spices; let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Fill the peppers with the rice mixture; top with grated cheese.
Place in a half inch of water in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until peppers are tender and cheese is browned, about 30 minutes.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Drop on waxed paper. Instant treats!

title: little brother's band banana smoothie(children's recipe)
directions: Will also need a blender and glass measuring cup.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli by package directions.
Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: After mashing potatoes, and while hot, add cream cheese, sour cream, butter, salt and pepper.
Whisk or beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole and sprinkle with Lawry's salt. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: dream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; mix in flour and nuts.
Shape into a ball.
Cut in half.
Color one with red food coloring and the other half with green food coloring.
Shape into small flat cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool and roll in granulated sugar.
Wonderful at Christmastime.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Mix first four ingredients in large cooking pot and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add noodles, tomatoes, parsley and basil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in your pie pan. Set aside.

title: glorified brownies with topping
directions: Melt butter.
Add cocoa and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Add salt and vanilla, then add flour. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add nuts and spread evenly in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Turn off oven.
Spread marshmallows over brownies and place back in oven until marshmallows are soft, but haven't lost shape. Spread topping over marshmallows.
Let brownies get cold before cutting.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball and pat into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stir together berries and 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine remaining sugar and all ingredients except whipped topping.
Mix well. Spread into a greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Let cake cool, then cut into squares.
Top with berries and whipped topping.

title: angel wings
directions: Mix ingredients. Chill dough 3 hours or overnight.
Roll out very thin. Cut into 1-inch strips 3 to 5 inches long.
Cut slit in center.
Pull one end of dough through slit.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hawaiian lemonade
directions: In a large bowl or pitcher, combine lemonade concentrate and 1 can water.
Add apricot nectar and pineapple juice.
Slowly pour ginger ale down side of bowl or pitcher.
Stir gently with an up and down motion to mix.

title: macaroni and ham
directions: Cook macaroni as package directions.
Drain.
Make a white sauce of the oleo, flour and milk.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, macaroni and ham.
Turn half the mixture into an oblong 2-quart baking dish.
Layer with half the cheese.
Add remaining macaroni and ham mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° until hot and golden, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: homemade chocolates
directions: Knead well the first 4 ingredients and vanilla.
Roll in small balls.
Put toothpick in top of each.
Place on cookie sheets lined with waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly.

title: molasses ginger cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Stir in molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda, cream of tartar and ginger.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with whipping cream, beginning and ending with flour. Mix after each addition.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Ice as desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix water, sugar, syrup and salt; cook to soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer).
Add peanuts to hard stage (300° or crack stage).
Take off heat.
Put in butter, soda and vanilla. Pour into buttered cookie sheet and spread.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: hershey pie
directions: Stir marshmallows and Hershey bars into hot milk.
When all are melted, cool.
Add Dream Whip.
Pour into a baked pie crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Combine pudding and Cool Whip. Place layer of crackers, then pudding mixture.
Repeat.
Last layer:
Frost crackers with frosting.
Refrigerate.

title: beef pot roast with sour cream
directions: Brown the beef in oil.
Add 1/4 cup sour cream, bay leaf, onions, carrots, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours, basting with additional sour cream to prevent burning.
Sprinkle flour over meat and turn it over.
Sprinkle with more flour.
If necessary, add more sour cream for the sauce. Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve the pot roast with noodles or potatoes and any kind of vegetables.

title: ham and cheese noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Put in a large mixing bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until cheese melts and casserole is heated through.

title: white chocolate  mousse
directions: Heat milk and blend in small pieces of chocolate.
Stir with wooden spoon until melted.
Set aside to cool.
Whip cream until stiff.
Beat egg whites and lemon juice until peaks form.
Fold whipped cream into chocolate mix gently.
Add egg whites.
Spoon into 8 dessert bowls.
Chill and garnish with sweet dark chocolate shavings.

title: buttermilk hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add onions, milk and beaten egg. Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat and fry to golden brown.
Drain and serve hot.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in small squares.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Blend all thoroughly.
Form into 2 logs. Roll in chili powder. Wrap in Saran Wrap or foil. Should make a couple days before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups hot boiling water over 1 cup oatmeal.
Let stand.
Mix the rest of ingredients together.
Add to oatmeal. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer chicken salad
directions: Cook rice according to package.
Cube cooked chicken.
Mix with rice and chill 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Gently mix together all ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together with mixer.
Add oregano and garlic powder.
Spread in bottom of a baking pan and cover with the pizza sauce.
Layer any topping you prefer on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (until bubbles around the edges).
Add Mozzarella cheese and return to oven for 5 minutes (until cheese is melted).
Let set about 5 minutes.
Dip is for tortilla chips or crackers.

title: brown-edged lemon wafers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix the butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in flour, almonds and the grated lemon rind.
Shape into 54 balls.
Put on greased cookie sheets, and with floured fingers, press each into thin 3-inch rounds.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes, until edges are brown.
Cool 1/2 minute on cookie sheets, then cool on racks.
Store in airtight container in a cool dry place.

title: tomato basil bread
directions: Proof yeast in 1/2 cup warm water along with the sugar (about 5 minutes).
Add proofed yeast to the rest of the ingredients and mix until dough sticks together enough to clean sides of the bowl. Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Let rise in greased bowl; punch down and shape into loaves.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Yields 2 regular size loaves or 4 mini loaves.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Thaw raspberries; reserve juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add cold water and juice.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Fold in cranberry sauce and raspberries.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add thawed strawberries, fruit cocktail, pineapple, nuts and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in mold greased with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until firm (only refrigerate Jell-O poured in mold).
Spread sour cream over mixture in mold.
Then spread the remaining Jell-O mixture over the sour cream layer and chill until firm.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown stew meat in oil, add onions and saute.
Add three cups water and beef bouillon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until beef is tender.
Slice mushrooms, add to beef.
Add 1 more cup of water, simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Add sour cream, then cornstarch to thicken.
Serve over boiled egg noodles.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese for added taste.

title: thai cashew chicken
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Fry the garlic, then add the dried chilies. Add the onion and heat until translucent.
Add the fish sauce and soy sauce.
Add the chicken and stir-fry until cooked through. Add cashews and heat 3 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add green onions.
Serve with steamed white rice.

title: marinated elk or venison roast
directions: Rinse thawed roast under cool water.
Place roast in large bowl; combine all ingredients together.
Pour over roast, turning roast several times.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight, turning 2 to 3 times.
Place meat in Dutch oven and pour the marinade over roast.
Cover and cook at 300° for 4 to 5 hours or until tender.
Baste occasionally.
Place meat on platter.
Add flour to remaining liquid; simmer, stir to thicken and serve as gravy.

title: vinegar candy(good for kids to make.)
directions: Boil together all ingredients until it becomes brittle when a small amount is tested in cold water.
Pour onto a buttered plate to cool, then pull with buttered fingers until snowy white.
Cut with scissors into manageable pieces.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Drain the pineapple, reserving the juice.

Sprinkle the brown sugar on the bottom of an 8-inch square baking pan that has been coated with nonstick vegetable spray. Place an even layer of drained pineapple over the brown sugar. Slice the cherries in half and arrange, cut side up, over the pineapple.

title: beef and chile rellenos bake
directions: Cook first four ingredients until meat is brown and drain. Drain chilies and cut in half.
Layer half of chilies and cheese in lightly greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with meat mixture. Top with remaining chilies and cheese,
